Subject: Codeforces Round 1023 (Div. 2)
Body: Hello, Jayceee1. Welcome to the regular Codeforces round.  I'm glad to invite you to take part in Codeforces Round 1023 (Div. 2). It starts on Monday, May, 5, 2025 14:35 (UTC). The contest duration is 2 hours 15 minutes. The allowed programming languages are C/C++, Pascal, Perl, Java, C#, Python (2 and 3), Ruby, PHP, Haskell, Scala, OCaml, D, Go, JavaScript and Kotlin.  Problems are prepared by auiunu, NahC0el and sunkuangzheng. Don't miss the round!  The round will be held on the rules of Codeforces, so read the rules (here and here) beforehand.  It will be for newcomers or participants from the second division (non-rated users or those having less than 2100 rating points). Want to compete? Do not forget to register for the contest and check your handle on the registrants page. The registration will be closed 5 minutes before the contest.  Register Now →  If you have any questions, please feel free to ask me on the pages of Codeforces. If you no longer wish to receive these emails, click https://codeforces.com/unsubscribe/contests/51474b72d79ac8ec8363936f1ca54cbe6dbb957a/ to unsubscribe.  Wish you high rating, MikeMirzayanov and Codeforces team

Or the kind where getting out of bed feels impossible? Or maybe you’re  feeling “blah” and don’t know why?   All of these highs, lows, and in-betweens are just a part of your unique  mental health journey. And it really is a journey.   In honor of Mental Health Awareness Month, we want to remind you that no  matter how fast or slow your progress feels today, you don’t need to be  anywhere other than right here (in all its messy, imperfect glory).   Just keep putting one foot in front of the other.    Give your mental health a boost with Calm — now 50% off  Celebrate Mental Health Awareness Month with 50% off Calm annual  subscriptions. Get all the tools you’ll need for your mental health journey,  now more affordable than ever.   Get 50% off now     New series for moms to help cultivate connection & get support      Jennifer Wallace, journalist and author, offers actionable tools to help moms  build resilience as caregivers and create a greater sense of community. These  bite-sized sessions are designed to listen to on the go, whether you’re sitting  in the driveway or hiding from your kids in the bathroom.   Unlock to listen     Calm to the Rescue  Content to help you take care of your mental health    Navigating the ups and downs        Daily Jay: Your Hero's Journey  Jay Shetty    As you progress on your mental health journey, it's completely normal to have  both great and not-so-great moments. Listen to this session to connect with how  obstacles and struggles are an essential part of our story.     Unlock with 50% Off     For when you're feeling behind        Daily Trip: Slow Burn  Jeff Warren    We’ve all set out to build a good habit like meditation, only to get  sidetracked by a new show or social media. If that sounds familiar, this  session offers a fresh way to refocus and stay on track.     Unlock with 50% Off    Calm Life         These 10 mental health goals will help you improve your wellbeing   Learn how setting mental health goals can improve your mental and emotional  wellbeing. Plus, 10 examples of mental health goals and how to create your own.     10 daily journal prompts to boost your mental health   Discover why daily journaling is a beneficial self-care practice on the  journey to better mental health and how to do it. Plus, 10 journal prompts,  topics, and ideas to get you started.      Keep this in mind     Remember: Slow and steady wins the mental health “race.” Small steps, deep  breaths. Reflect: How is your mental health feeling from 1-10? What could bump you up a  point? Reframe: I’m falling behind. → Mental health isn’t linear. Ups and downs are  part of the journey.    Inhale ease, exhale stress            Have a question? Last year, we launched Notion Calendar to help you better manage your most valuable resource—time. Now, we’re rethinking another daily tool that shapes our lives. Email.  Email hasn’t changed in decades! It’s noisy, tedious to manage, and definitely not beautiful.  With Notion Mail, your inbox thinks like you. It organizes itself, drafts your emails, and schedules meetings exactly how you would. It’s flexible (like Notion!) so you can make it your own.  Give it a try. We hope it brings some joy to your inbox!  Connect your Gmail ( https://mail.notion.so/?utm_campaign=notionmail%3A+What%27s+New+2.50+-+Notion+Mail+%28Phase+2%29&utm_campaignid=641&utm_campaigntype=behavioral&utm_content=Email+1+%28Students%29&utm_medium=email_action&utm_source=customer.io )  ****************************** Stay focused with custom views ******************************  Split your inbox into custom views that show different focus areas. Sort your views by topic, urgency, sender, or any way you need to stay distraction-free.  Stay focused with custom views ( https://mail.notion.so/?utm_campaign=notionmail%3A+What%27s+New+2.50+-+Notion+Mail+%28Phase+2%29&utm_campaignid=641&utm_campaigntype=behavioral&utm_content=Email+1+%28Students%29&utm_medium=email_action&utm_source=customer.io )  ******************************** Never write the same email twice ********************************  Use snippets to create email templates that you can reuse in a click. You can even include attachments and scheduling links! I have snippets for introductions, follow-up messages, and thank-you notes. Perfect for when you’re in cold outreach mode.  Never write the same email twice ( https://mail.notion.so/?utm_campaign=notionmail%3A+What%27s+New+2.50+-+Notion+Mail+%28Phase+2%29&utm_campaignid=641&utm_campaigntype=behavioral&utm_content=Email+1+%28Students%29&utm_medium=email_action&utm_source=customer.io )  *************************** Schedule meetings instantly ***************************  We are finally putting an end to the back-and-forth of booking a meeting! Notion Calendar integrates with Notion Mail—just type /schedule, mark your availability, and let others pick a time. Get Notion Calendar free → ( https://www.notion.com/product/calendar?utm_campaign=notionmail%3A+What%27s+New+2.50+-+Notion+Mail+%28Phase+2%29&utm_campaignid=641&utm_campaigntype=behavioral&utm_content=Email+1+%28Students%29&utm_medium=email_action&utm_source=customer.io )  Schedule meetings instantly ( https://www.notion.com/product/calendar?utm_campaign=notionmail%3A+What%27s+New+2.50+-+Notion+Mail+%28Phase+2%29&utm_campaignid=641&utm_campaigntype=behavioral&utm_content=Email+1+%28Students%29&utm_medium=email_action&utm_source=customer.io )  *************************** Organize your inbox with AI ***************************  Tell Notion AI what types of emails are important toauto label, and it will sort them as they arrive. We’ve been testing auto-labeling with early users, and it’s a crowd favorite! This is a new AI feature that will get smarter over time, so please send us your feedback.  Organize your inbox with AI ( https://mail.notion.so/?utm_campaign=notionmail%3A+What%27s+New+2.50+-+Notion+Mail+%28Phase+2%29&utm_campaignid=641&utm_campaigntype=behavioral&utm_content=Email+1+%28Students%29&utm_medium=email_action&utm_source=customer.io )  ****************************** Write beautiful emails, faster ******************************  Just like Notion, you can type / to use your favorite content blocks! You can also prompt AI using your space bar. Use it to draft follow-up emails that use your Notion docs for context or just to polish your writing.  Write beautiful emails, faster ( https://mail.notion.so/?utm_campaign=notionmail%3A+What%27s+New+2.50+-+Notion+Mail+%28Phase+2%29&utm_campaignid=641&utm_campaigntype=behavioral&utm_content=Email+1+%28Students%29&utm_medium=email_action&utm_source=customer.io )  ************************************************** My favorite comments from early users (thank you!) **************************************************  Write beautiful emails, faster ( https://mail.notion.so/?utm_campaign=notionmail%3A+What%27s+New+2.50+-+Notion+Mail+%28Phase+2%29&utm_campaignid=641&utm_campaigntype=behavioral&utm_content=Email+1+%28Students%29&utm_medium=email_action&utm_source=customer.io )  Connect your Gmail ( https://mail.notion.so/?utm_campaign=notionmail%3A+What%27s+New+2.50+-+Notion+Mail+%28Phase+2%29&utm_campaignid=641&utm_campaigntype=behavioral&utm_content=Email+1+%28Students%29&utm_medium=email_action&utm_source=customer.io )  This is just the beginning! Keep the feedback coming—you can direct message us at @NotionMail ( https://x.com/NotionMail?utm_campaign=notionmail%3A+What%27s+New+2.50+-+Notion+Mail+%28Phase+2%29&utm_campaignid=641&utm_campaigntype=behavioral&utm_content=Email+1+%28Students%29&utm_medium=email_action&utm_source=customer.io ) or email us at team@makenotion.com ( team@makenotion.com?utm_campaign=notionmail%3A+What%27s+New+2.50+-+Notion+Mail+%28Phase+2%29&utm_campaignid=641&utm_campaigntype=behavioral&utm_content=Email+1+%28Students%29&utm_medium=email_action&utm_source=customer.io )—and we’ll keep shipping improvements.  Enjoy! Ivan  P.S. Download the Notion Mail desktop app ( http://notion.com/product/mail/download?utm_campaign=notionmail%3A+What%27s+New+2.50+-+Notion+Mail+%28Phase+2%29&utm_campaignid=641&utm_campaigntype=behavioral&utm_content=Email+1+%28Students%29&utm_medium=email_action&utm_source=customer.io ) for free now (it works offline, too!). The iOS app and a unified inbox to bring your work and life together are on their way—you’ll be the first to know.  P.P.S. If you haven’t already, download the Notion Calendar app ( https://www.notion.com/product/calendar/download?utm_campaign=notionmail%3A+What%27s+New+2.50+-+Notion+Mail+%28Phase+2%29&utm_campaignid=641&utm_campaigntype=behavioral&utm_content=Email+1+%28Students%29&utm_medium=email_action&utm_source=customer.io ) for free, too. We love how your docks are looking! 👀  Visuals showing some early comments about Notion Mail ( https://mail.notion.so/?utm_campaign=notionmail%3A+What%27s+New+2.50+-+Notion+Mail+%28Phase+2%29&utm_campaignid=641&utm_campaigntype=behavioral&utm_content=Email+1+%28Students%29&utm_medium=email_action&utm_source=customer.io )  Write, plan, organize. In one AI-powered workspace. Subject: [Dreamhack] Golden Week, Buddha’s Birthday, and Dreamhack CTF
Body: Dreamhack CTF Season 7 #9 < The day of Buddha’s birth >       Hello, Jaycelation,  Greetings from Dreamhack, the hacker’s playground!    Got any plans for the Golden Week?  Spend just one day with Dreamhack CTF - and turn your break into something truly rewarding and fun!      The first Dreamhack CTF of May is coming your way on May 3rd.  This Div1 round is packed with challenging problems — perfect for making your Saturday meaningful and productive. Show off your skills and try to grab an exclusive Dreamhack umbrella!   * 🗓️ Schedule   * 2025/05/03 09:00 ~ 23:59 (15hrs, UTC+9)    * 🚩 Eligibility   * All Dreamhack Members    * ❓ Challenge Categories   * Pwnable(Crypto), Reversing, Web, Crypto    * ☂️ Prizes   * Dreamhack Umbrella   * 1 CTF Winner    * 4 Lucky Draws (Min. 1 solve required!)    * Prize draws will be held at the #dh-ctf-season7 channel of the   [Dreamhack  Official Discord server]  https://discord.gg/dreamhackio   .   We can’t wait to see you all in action!  Happy Hacking!  - The Dreamhack Team    [Click to Participate] https://dreamhack.io/ctf/663  This email was sent to all Dreamhack members. Subject: Truy cập lại vào tài khoản Spotify
Body: Chào Jayce!   Chào mừng bạn quay lại Spotify. Để hoàn tất quá trình đăng nhập, hãy chọn nút bên dưới trên thiết bị di động. Đường liên kết này có hiệu lực trong 4 giờ.    CHUYỂN ĐẾN SPOTIFY ( https://accounts.spotify.com/login/ott/music#token=g8_76OcwRaigrpAoVuceLw&passwordToken=3QEU2o-2Spe44IzFjahRRg&username=31jet66akg6cnlwxttqoxqeqvizu&continue=https%3A%2F%2Faccounts.spotify.com%2Fpassword-reset%2Fcomplete%233QEU2o-2Spe44IzFjahRRg )   https://accounts.spotify.com/login/ott/music#token=g8_76OcwRaigrpAoVuceLw&passwordToken=3QEU2o-2Spe44IzFjahRRg&username=31jet66akg6cnlwxttqoxqeqvizu&continue=https%3A%2F%2Faccounts.spotify.com%2Fpassword-reset%2Fcomplete%233QEU2o-2Spe44IzFjahRRg ( https://accounts.spotify.com/login/ott/music#token=g8_76OcwRaigrpAoVuceLw&passwordToken=3QEU2o-2Spe44IzFjahRRg&username=31jet66akg6cnlwxttqoxqeqvizu&continue=https%3A%2F%2Faccounts.spotify.com%2Fpassword-reset%2Fcomplete%233QEU2o-2Spe44IzFjahRRg )   Đường liên kết này cũng xác nhận email liên kết với tài khoản của bạn.   Nếu bạn không tìm cách đăng nhập vào tài khoản của mình hoặc không yêu cầu email này thì đừng lo lắng, có thể bạn đã nhập địa chỉ email này do nhầm lẫn. Bạn chỉ cần bỏ qua hoặc xóa email này rồi sử dụng mật khẩu hiện tại của mình để đăng nhập.   Chúc bạn nghe nhạc vui vẻ!   Nhóm Spotify   -------------  Mua Spotify cho:   * iPhone (https://itunes.apple.com/app/spotify-music/id324684580)   * iPad (https://itunes.apple.com/app/spotify-music/id324684580)   * Android (https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.spotify.music)   * Khác (https://www.spotify.com/download/)  Thư này đã được gửi tới jaycedang0601@gmail.com.  Nếu bạn có câu hỏi hay khiếu nại nào, vui lòng liên hệ với chúng tôi ( https://www.spotify.com/about-us/contact/ ).    * Điều khoản sử dụng https://www.spotify.com/legal/end-user-agreement/   * Chính sách quyền riêng tư https://www.spotify.com/legal/privacy-policy/   * Liên hệ với chúng tôi https://www.spotify.com/about-us/contact/   Spotify AB, Regeringsgatan 19, 111 53, Stockholm, Sweden

Subject: 🔥 Dreamhack Subscription Officially Launched – See Which Plan Fits You Best!
Body: Hey Jaycelation,  Greetings from Dreamhack, the hacker’s playground!    We’re thrilled to share that our new Dreamhack subscription is officially live! This marks the first step toward becoming a more structured and hands-on cybersecurity learning platform. Here’s what’s changed—and how you can benefit from the new plans.  🔍 What’s New?   * Three subscription plans: Choose from Starter, Pro, or Expert based on your  current skills and learning goals.    * Streamlined Unit-based content: We’ve transformed our previous roadmap into  smaller, focused Units—making learning more flexible and efficient.    * Faster content updates: New Units reflect the latest vulnerabilities, attack  techniques, and security trends—updated more frequently than ever.    * Hands-on Lab Exercises: Learn by doing with real-world attack simulations in  a controlled environment.    * Free Wargame Access with VM credits: Even without a subscription, you can  launch up to 3 VMs per week—credits reset weekly and are restored upon  successful completion.   👉 For full details, check the  [[official announcement].] https://dreamhack.io/board/notice/258?utm_source=mail&utm_campaign=subscription-launch  ✅ Subscription Plans & Launch Discounts (Annual Billing)  We’ve designed three subscription tiers based on how you learn and grow:   * Starter   * [75% OFF] – From ₩19,600/month → ₩4,900/month    * Perfect for beginners exploring cybersecurity and ethical hacking.    * Includes: Tier 0 – Tier 1 Units / Unlimited VMs / Vulnerability Tags    * Pro   * [50% OFF] – From ₩40,000/month → ₩20,000/month    * Ideal for learners ready to dive deeper with structured paths and  real-world scenarios.    * Includes: Tier 0 – Tier 3 Units / Early access to new Units / Lab / Q&A  Tickets    * Expert   * [50% OFF] – From ₩80,000/month → ₩40,000/month    * Designed for those aiming to master the highest level of offensive  security.    * Includes: Full access to Tier 0 – Tier 4 (Tier 4 is exclusive) /  Conference Invitation (Annual)   From hands-on wargames and structured learning paths to expert-level content, Dreamhack’s new subscription plans are designed to match your goals and help you level up faster.    ※ Discounts apply to annual subscriptions only. ※ For full details, please check the official announcement and event terms. ※ We’re also preparing global payment options to support users worldwide—stay tuned for updates!    Happy Hacking!  - The Dreamhack Team    [Check Out Plans & Subscribe Now] https://dreamhack.io/payments/membership-pricing?utm_source=mail&utm_campaign=subscription-launch  This email was sent to all Dreamhack members. Subject: Codeforces Round 1022 (Div. 2)
Body: Hello, Jayceee1. Welcome to the regular Codeforces round.  I'm glad to invite you to take part in Codeforces Round 1022 (Div. 2). It starts on Thursday, May, 1, 2025 14:35 (UTC). The contest duration is 2 hours. The allowed programming languages are C/C++, Pascal, Perl, Java, C#, Python (2 and 3), Ruby, PHP, Haskell, Scala, OCaml, D, Go, JavaScript and Kotlin.  Problems are prepared by eugenechka.boyko.2_0-0, m3tr0 and suprend. Don't miss the round!  The round will be held on the rules of Codeforces, so read the rules (here and here) beforehand.  It will be for newcomers or participants from the second division (non-rated users or those having less than 2100 rating points). Want to compete? Do not forget to register for the contest and check your handle on the registrants page. The registration will be closed 5 minutes before the contest.  Register Now →  If you have any questions, please feel free to ask me on the pages of Codeforces. If you no longer wish to receive these emails, click https://codeforces.com/unsubscribe/contests/51474b72d79ac8ec8363936f1ca54cbe6dbb957a/ to unsubscribe.  Wish you high rating, MikeMirzayanov and Codeforces team

Subject: Gitpod-hosted compute coming this summer, VS Code in the browser, user secrets shipped
Body: ( https://www.gitpod.io/?utm_campaign=newsletter&utm_source=customerio&utm_medium=email ) Hey there,     Tl;dr of this issue:  * An update on Gitpod’s product offerings * Gitpod-hosted compute is coming this summer * VS Code Browser support now available * User secrets now supported And our latest content releases like the platform engineering resource library, an article from our CTO on agentic software development, and more.  Happy reading!     *************** Product updates ***************  -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Naming is hard ( http://www.gitpod.io/blog/naming-is-hard?utm_campaign=newsletter&utm_source=customerio&utm_medium=email ) --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  Back in October, we introduced 'Flex' to represent a major shift in Gitpod’s architecture. But naming is hard and sometimes what starts as a label for a new architecture and pricing tier becomes a source of confusion. So we’re simplifying and dropping the name ‘Flex’.  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Gitpod-hosted compute is coming this summer ( https://www.gitpod.io/blog/coming-soon-gitpod-as-a-saas?utm_campaign=newsletter&utm_source=customerio&utm_medium=email ) ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  We’re launching a fully-hosted SaaS this summer through our new Core tier, complementing existing deployment options of running locally via Gitpod Desktop or self-hosting. Start instantly with pre-configured dev environments on high-spec CPUs/GPUs, without any infrastructure setup. Join the waitlist ( https://www.gitpod.io/blog/coming-soon-gitpod-as-a-saas?utm_campaign=newsletter&utm_source=customerio&utm_medium=email#:~:text=Gitpod%2Dhosted%20compute.-,Feature%20waitlist,-Email ) to get early access.  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- VS Code in the Browser support ( https://www.gitpod.io/changelog/gitpod-supports-vscode-browser?utm_campaign=newsletter&utm_source=customerio&utm_medium=email ) ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  Gitpod now supports VS Code in the browser in addition to regular desktop IDEs and editors. It has terminals and all other features of VS Code Desktop. Just port over your settings via ‘settings sync’.  ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ User secrets support ( https://www.gitpod.io/changelog/user-secrets-support-in-gitpod?utm_campaign=newsletter&utm_source=customerio&utm_medium=email ) ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  Configure personal secrets for all of your environments and integrate against third-party systems that use Personal Access Tokens to authenticate seamlessly. Mount these as files or inject them as environment variables.  ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ JetBrains Toolbox App support ( https://www.gitpod.io/changelog/gitpod-supports-jetbrains-toolbox?utm_campaign=newsletter&utm_source=customerio&utm_medium=email ) ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  The JetBrains Toolbox App now supports remote development in Gitpod, allowing you to manage IDEs, connect to Gitpod environments, and install or update IDEs from your desktop.     ************** Latest content **************  ( https://www.gitpod.io/platform-engineer?utm_campaign=newsletter&utm_source=customerio&utm_medium=email )  ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ Platform Engineering resource library ( https://www.gitpod.io/platform-engineer?utm_campaign=newsletter&utm_source=customerio&utm_medium=email ) ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  Everything you need to know about becoming a better platform engineer and improving developer experience. We’ve got articles and reports from how to fix ‘works on my machine’ issues to replacing VDI, and latest trends in Platform Engineering.  ( https://www.gitpod.io/blog/time-between-disengagements-the-rise-of-the-software-conductor?utm_campaign=newsletter&utm_source=customerio&utm_medium=email )  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- The rise of the software conductor ( https://www.gitpod.io/blog/time-between-disengagements-the-rise-of-the-software-conductor?utm_campaign=newsletter&utm_source=customerio&utm_medium=email ) -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  As agents enter the workforce, software engineers will become software conductors. Read from our CTO about how to measure autonomy in the age of AI software development, inspired by autonomous vehicles.  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Build smarter with infrastructure for AI and humans ( https://www.gitpod.io/solutions/ai?utm_campaign=newsletter&utm_source=customerio&utm_medium=email ) ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  Use Gitpod to run AI coding agents in isolated development environments that reduce the blast radius of rogue agents, making experimentation safer by default. Deploy remote MCP servers, scale agent workloads without managing infrastructure, and equip your entire team with secure environments that are ready in seconds.  ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Improve developer experience and security posture by replacing VDI using Gitpod + Island ( https://www.gitpod.io/blog/replace-vdi-with-gitpod-and-island?utm_campaign=newsletter&utm_source=customerio&utm_medium=email ) -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  Using Gitpod for development and accessing it via Island, an enterprise browser, lets you replace VDI securely for all development workflows without a full-blown remote desktop setup.     *************** Upcoming events ***************  * AWS Summit Dubai, May 21, 2025 - Booth S7 in the Dubai World Trade Center * AI Engineer World Fair SF, June 3 - 5, 2025 * Platform Con London & New York, June 25 & 26, 2025 - Join our workshop on "Build, buy, trial or wait? Platform engineering roadmapping for AI". * AWS Summit NYC, July 16, 2025 * Platform Day KubeCon Atlanta, November 10, 2025 * AWS re:Invent Las Vegas, December 1 - 5, 2025   Happy reading!  Talia  X ( https://twitter.com/gitpod ) GitHub ( https://github.com/gitpod-io ) Book a Demo ( https://www.gitpod.io/contact/get-demo?utm_campaign=newsletter&utm_source=customerio&utm_medium=email ) · Docs ( https://www.gitpod.io/docs?utm_campaign=newsletter&utm_source=customerio&utm_medium=email ) · Blog ( https://www.gitpod.io/blog?utm_campaign=newsletter&utm_source=customerio&utm_medium=email ) · Contact ( https://www.gitpod.io/contact?utm_campaign=newsletter&utm_source=customerio&utm_medium=email )  ( https://www.gitpod.io/?utm_campaign=newsletter&utm_source=customerio&utm_medium=email )© 2024 Gitpod GmbH. All rights reserved.  This email was sent to jaycedang0601@gmail.com. To no longer receive these emails, unsubscribe here ( http://track.customer.io/unsubscribe/dgTivgYDAO-KWO6KWAGWhzqXacJB5qbGoYE1mNk= ).

BlackHoodie's goal is to create a space for women to enter the security space, learn skills that are otherwise expensive, find their interests and grow a professional network.  BlackHoodie @ OffensiveCon 2025 (https://hub.hex-rays.com/e3t/Ctc/ZX+113/djVGn-04/VWCHGB37B9WQW3lGGZr3sfYqmW8kTzPf5w05TTN6WXHZ-3prCCW7Y8-PT6lZ3n9V-PkKS2xlZ45W5_cJdK85ZNjNW6PsYCL4LKGZQW1WNq8R8JXlpfW8ysFG93Kwc-KW5WnxFK6dBzlcW8J9jy_2bWQh6W6Xc2w0246N7GW3mZkDG8rwZy8W6bKW-53P1b5DN1YTgP6CCMMTW1Gv1xT1dWz66W5tc-pm1wtrS1W8PNp8B6QhvmSW76p2Xc4JkdPWW1vDwt69cYqzYW7HykdV25vJW6W985KYp6c-M3qW8R1kcD7xt0PGW4KwL1d4lCl-3W7nnNVy1899T5VCx1M38m4f6YN6_HcYr_65qwW3Q_W1c1-Cx_VW6MNn3C7xzsJ6W6x6XkK38nmDff99_H9F04 )  OffensiveCon 2025 | Berlin, Germany | 16-17 May  TRAINING: Rolf Rolles will lead a 4-day course focused on C++ features commonly encountered in binaries, their implementation details, and how to handle them in IDA. This course will cover Hex-Rays tools in-depth. Check out the full details here (https://hub.hex-rays.com/e3t/Ctc/ZX+113/djVGn-04/VWCHGB37B9WQW3lGGZr3sfYqmW8kTzPf5w05TTN6WXHYv5m_5PW50kH_H6lZ3lWW99B6126xCzK3W71rpFV6gRXvqW3jh9hY3KmJRwW2PfZtn3lx-XTW8WjgN71yFy7LN1mWxr0F7stQVLY5Lr4RzY-7W2ryYzS5SW35VW5-yrHH6kTHYfN38ryZB9v-dJW7pSPXB4TgpBnW7XxPs67wfsKRW316mQ813Dl0fW4LnCYL8vkPjyW32wjwY7WM6zFVgjF1b5_vwvJN5ftV396Yjr6N1mybP_b6h0mW7HzTBz6vXYZnN5GFxgC9SlvPW2kkN8J60JZ4zVPtFtj5cPV8PW6nNm4g7FwFQZW22nGzk3fWKXQW2BzcXs6lr8mQW4jzHD25NTklQW86j3lC8JSBcDW2036yK4HQzxJW8sjjKT5v9RqdW2yjPd46mSthJW6vgyBR8wfNz3W5zfD291_0v0Nf3l32dM04 ) . BIZ DISCUSSIONS: If you're an enterprise customer—or considering becoming one—we'd love to meet. Let's talk about your current usage, upcoming projects, and new features on our roadmap that could support your goals.  Book a meeting (https://hub.hex-rays.com/e3t/Ctc/ZX+113/djVGn-04/VWCHGB37B9WQW3lGGZr3sfYqmW8kTzPf5w05TTN6WXH-z3prCCW95jsWP6lZ3lSW2fVvn77VJ3QdN4BF3H-jLF2cW7GJj-q6vMgNpW48CrfD21lwbMW9l6mc34-3YLlW7Lh31Q8fSqS_N3PWCh7cKb0ZW8Mrm8j1zzgKWW4S6KNb33-GQTW1H0tNV90QZJFW8XMP8Y5-k2xnW3BKrQ76vTYRwV1dlyf1cQRJJW2c6n3s7Hz2_yW6hGDBT3SrDg3W5KDXPs355K7CW46KxNN2jKLzYW5G20kP5k4kSqW1nZWy01SKS-YW3cm-Bc2TjLXGW3qbLvg3NW3VsW77FV6S7fjkZcW5m1Hl26r4bVSW1TZbcH2jzv6CW8syVg47vG2MbW74Y2nf8Q2pNnV_9yWn1pDjC6W5s8fql3mFypxW6H_ffY1p-yfNN7TD8BlMzrRHf6pS_jH04 ) with us to learn about upcoming features and more. Subject: GitHub Copilot: What’s in your free plan 🤖
Body: Welcome to GitHub Copilot. Here’s how to get started.  You now have access to GitHub Copilot in VS Code and github.com for free as part of your GitHub user account—and that includes support for models from OpenAI and Anthropic.  Ask Copilot how to get started >: https://github.com/copilot  What’s included    - 2,000 intelligent code completions a month. Get context-aware code suggestions that draw context from your GitHub projects and VS Code workspace.   - 50 Copilot Chat messages a month. Ask Copilot for help understanding code, refactoring something, or debugging an issue.   - Choose your AI model. Pick between Claude 3.5 Sonnet or OpenAI GPT-4o.   - Make changes to multiple files with Copilot Edits. Tackle changes across multiple files with Copilot Edits.   - Support for the Copilot Extensions ecosystem. Access third-party agents designed for tasks such as querying Stack Overflow or searching the web with Perplexity.   - Choose where you build. Enjoy support in VS Code and across GitHub.  So, what will you build?  P.S. - Not sure where to start? Try these Copilot Chat prompts >: https://docs.github.com/en/copilot/example-prompts-for-github-copilot-chat  Copilot Settings  GitHub Copilot will show code suggestions that match public code including code references in the VS Code and github.com experience: https://docs.github.com/en/copilot/using-github-copilot/finding-public-code-that-matches-github-copilot-suggestions GitHub and affiliates may use your data for product improvement. You can adjust both data use and public matching code suggestion settings in your Copilot Settings: https://github.com/settings/copilot. Subject: Accenture Data & AI Week: Almost here!
Body: A 5 day immersive workshop session              Take control of AI before it takes control of your career! If you wish to pursue a career in the world of Data Science, AI, Deep Learning & ML, then this week is the perfect stepping stone for you! We're thrilled to invite you to "Accenture's Data & AI week" -  5 days of 5 power packed sessions starting from 5th MayEvents you can't afford to miss:  May 5: Discover how agentic AI is transforming enterprises May 6: See AI in action across industries worldwide May 7: Learn practical scaling strategies with ML Ops & Gen AI Ops May 8: Level Up with Gen AI & Data May 9: Chart your career path in the Data & AI landscape  From thought-provoking panels to hands-on workshops, every session is designed to connect you with industry leaders and cutting-edge insights. Plus, your details will be shared with the Accenture Hiring Team for their future processes! So, what are you waiting for? The future isn't going to hack itself! Reinvent your career, pioneer solutions, and shape the future of AIWe look forward to seeing you there..         Register for free         Limited seats are left for each session, so hurry up!                                Write to us: courses@geeksforgeeks.orgCoding is not my cup of tea. so I'll Unsubscribe

Subject: [QC] TẶNG ĐẾN 200.000 VND CÙNG VIETCOMBANK CONNECT24 VÀ APPLE PAY
Issue 275: Platform agnostic
Body: Community roadmap, rogue caps locks, and debugging in space ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌          30 April    Complexity is one of those things that computer science and software  engineering has sought to reduce over time. No, don't laugh, I'm serious. While  new techs may come in and make our lives messier, soon the industry turns its  mind towards simplifications: standards, reusable components,  platform-independent solutions, and so on.  We've got a lot of conversations for you along those lines. In the latest  Leaders of Code podcast, Popper chats with Prashanth Chandrasekar, CEO of Stack  Overflow, and guests from Lloyds Banking Group about how to simplify and  standardize a complex engineering org. On the main podcast, we have chats with  the CEO of Dataiku about simplifying the data to genAI pipeline, and with Laly  Bar-Ilan, Chief Scientist at Bit, about how they are using genAI to create  reusable components, not code.  And in the questions and links, we're dropping knowledge you didn't even know  you needed. Is women and children first a discriminatory policy? Can you host  your blog on a Wii? Are millennials also flat earthers? Would you buy a  computer from a raccoon?     From the blog   Standardization and simplification as key to engineering excellence    stackoverflow.blog In this episode of Leaders of Code, we chat with guests from Lloyds Banking  Group about their focus on engineering excellence and the need for  organizations to adapt to new technologies while ensuring customer safety and  meeting their expectations.  Community Products roadmap update, April 2025   stackoverflow.blog An update on recent launches and the upcoming roadmap  Visually orchestrating data diagnostics but platform agnostic   stackoverflow.blog Ryan chats with Dataiku CEO and cofounder Florian Douetteau about the  complexities of the genAI data stack and how his company is orchestrating it.  Generating components, not tokens   stackoverflow.blog On today’s episode, Ben and Ryan chat with Laly Bar-Ilan, Chief Scientist at  Bit.     Interesting questions   Caps Lock keeps turning on in each application separately   askubuntu.com OR YOU COULD JUST EMBRACE YELLING ALL THE TIME.  Does offering women and children first priority for limited places on a  lifeboat breach discrimination law?   law.stackexchange.com “In this case, saving the lives of children would constitute a legitimate aim  as they are generally more vulnerable than adults and weaker swimmers than  adults.”  Are a third of American Millennials flat Earthers?   skeptics.stackexchange.com One-third know the Earth isn't perfectly round and is actually an oblate  spheroid.  How would a plant disconnected to the ground get nitrogen?   worldbuilding.stackexchange.com The same way plants connected to the ground do; dissolved in water.     Links from around the web   The Gruen Transfer is consuming the internet    sebs.website The internet is becoming more disorienting by design.  This blog is hosted on a Nintendo Wii   blog.infected.systems It's the opposite of an emulator.  How we diagnosed and fixed the 2023 Voyager 1 anomaly from 15 billion miles  away    www.youtube.com Debugging becomes way harder when you have 45 hours of latency between command  and response.  The raccoons who made computer magazine ads great    technologizer.com Raccoons were a lot like early PC users: dark circles around their eyes, ate  garbage, and occasionally hid in the attic.   Onboard, organize, and bring your team up to speed in a jiffy. Try Stack  Overflow for Teams   . Subject: Attackers are gunning for your blind spots. Are you looking the right way? 👾
Body: ThreatReady  By Hack The Box   By Hack The Box                Read this article on LinkedIn to join the conversation Read on LinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/comm/pulse/attackers-gunning-your-blind-spots-you-looking-right-way-hackthebox-isplf?lipi=urn%3Ali%3Apage%3Aemail_email_series_follow_newsletter_01%3BDO5EsCyYRYy%2BcEYTUVH%2FOw%3D%3D&midToken=AQEMCMuQJusoZg&midSig=2xDG2gUygm1bM1&trk=eml-email_series_follow_newsletter_01-null-0-read_more_banner_cta_&trkEmail=eml-email_series_follow_newsletter_01-null-0-read_more_banner_cta_-null-i8mwdi~ma2op7mb~sw-null-null&eid=i8mwdi-ma2op7mb-sw&otpToken=MTMwNDFlZTIxYTI3Y2ZjMGJjMjgwZmViNDExYWUyYmQ4YmNmZDg0NDlkYWQ4NjZiN2JjZjA1NjY0OTVkNWJmMGYzZDZkN2U5NDVkNWMxODc2Mzg1YTg4YjJjZWQxZWQ1OGQwYzllODU0YjQ1OTUwNWU3MzBiMmY2LDEsMQ%3D%3D    We are BACK with the April edition of ThreatReady—and boy, is this one a doozy. From silent-but-deadly breaches in the supply chain to AI slipping into the hands of attackers, the threat landscape isn’t just evolving, it’s actually outpacing the way many organizations approach cyber readiness. So we’ve done the legwork, sifted through the noise, and surfaced the insights that actually matter for your teams. Let’s go. 🧠 CVE gets its funding—but the uncertainty remains The CVE Program doesn’t make headlines often, but maybe it should. It’s the connective tissue that ties together the vulnerabilities we see in the wild and the defensive action that follows. So when CISA affirmed its commitment to funding it this month amid rumours to the contrary, there was a collective sigh of relief—but it’s a stark reminder of just how fragile the system is. “Without stable, well-funded CVE infrastructure, the entire cybersecurity industry loses the connective tissue that links real-world threats to effective defensive action,” said Haris Pylarinos, Founder & CEO at Hack The Box. This isn’t just about visibility. If the CVE system falters, the effects trickle down: Security teams train on outdated or incomplete intel Simulations lack realism Patch timelines slow down Coordinated threat response stalls And the impact hits hard at the training level. HTB’s platform, like many others, relies on CVE and MITRE ATT&CK data to replicate real-world attack paths and build out threat simulations that actually reflect what’s happening on the ground. “The uncertainty around future funding doesn’t just threaten visibility into vulnerabilities,” Haris explains, “it also undermines the realism and effectiveness of crucial training exercises, including purple teaming and threat simulations.” This is what makes the CVE Program more than a registry—it’s an enabler of long-term cyber resilience. A consistent, reliable CVE system keeps everyone on the same page: vendors, defenders, incident responders, educators. “We need long-term investment and a stable governance model for these foundational assets,” Haris adds, “or we risk stagnating the very systems that protect us.” Bottom line: the CVE Program is safe—for now. Unless that lifeline becomes a real, long-term commitment, the entire security ecosystem is sitting on sand. 🌟 Put your organization in the cyber spotlight  Want to stand out before some of the biggest brains in cybersecurity? Here’s one way to do it—join our team of sponsors for our highly anticipated Global Cyber Skills Benchmark: Operation Blackout, happening this May 23-27. Sponsoring an HTB CTF like this one means more than just exposure; it’s a way of showing the world you’ve got a security-first mindset. In a nutshell: being a sponsor will boost your employer brand, help you attract top-notch talent, and be associated with events beloved by the infosec community.  💚 Join our team of sponsors 💚 👾 They’re in your third parties (and you might not even know it) Let’s talk about supply chain threats. Again. Because they’re not going away any time soon. According to the SecurityScorecard’s 2025 Global Third-Party Breach Report, a staggering 35.5% of all breaches in 2024 involved third-party vendors. More worryingly than that,  41.4% of ransomware attacks now come through a vendor, rather than through the targeted organization directly.  A lack of visibility is partly to blame here. As much as 61% of organizations experienced a supply chain attack in the past year, with many of them having no knowledge of the exposure until after the breach had already hit their shores. But what does that mean for you? For starters, remember that your attack posture isn’t just defined by what you manage. It includes everything from vendors and SaaS tools to any platforms teams across your organization rely on to do their jobs.  Don’t look at supply chain security as someone else’s problem; take a proactive approach. Carry out third-party risk assessments. Ask the hard questions, and don’t assume your vendors are doing it right—verify that they are. 🛡️ How to protect your org from third-party supply chain breaches While you can’t control your vendors’ security, you can limit your exposure should they experience a breach. Here’s how to shore up your defenses:  1. Vet before you buy: Make security due diligence part of your procurement process. Ask for policies, incident history, and third-party audit reports. Then revisit that info regularly—not just at onboarding. 2. Get it in writing: Your contracts should include security clauses, breach notification timelines, and audit rights. If a vendor drops the ball, you need the leverage to act. 3. Monitor in real time: Point-in-time reviews won’t cut it. Use tools or services that continuously monitor your vendors’ risk posture—think attack surface scanning, patching cadence, or exposed credentials. 4. Prep your people: Your people are often your first line of defense. Provide regular training to help them recognize risks in your supply chain and know how to escalate issues ASAP.  5. Put the right training in place: HTB’s Supply Chain Attacks module covers how these attacks really happen—from poisoned repos to hardware backdoors—and how to spot them before they get out of hand. 📌 Psst. You can check out NIST's SP 800-161 and CISA's defensive playbook for deeper guidance. TL;DR: Treat your vendors like part of your own infrastructure, because when they fall, you’ll feel the impact too. Remember: your security posture is only as strong as its weakest link. 💡 How CTF results can shape your talent strategy Just in case you missed it, we recently shared some key insights on how CTF results and benchmarking data can inform long-term cybersecurity workforce strategies. By analyzing trends in CTF performance, organizations are better equipped to identify skills gaps, scope out areas for improvement, and create more targeted development plans. Key takeaways from the discussion include: CTF data helps pinpoint the skills most needed in real-world scenarios; Understanding performance trends allows for focused, effective upskilling; A data-driven approach to workforce development can significantly reduce training time and boost team readiness. If you’re looking for ways to apply these insights to your own workforce planning, or want to get the full picture check out the blog post or watch the webinar on demand.  🚨 Headlines you shouldn’t scroll past The aviation world is facing a new kind of turbulence—and it’s got nothing to do with bad weather. From GPS spoofing over Eastern Europe to explosives-laced cargo incidents, the skies are getting riskier. Researchers have already shown how spoofed aircraft data could trick navigation systems or trigger fake collision alerts. The threat? Very real. The fix? Still patchy. How can aviation security catch up? Encrypted apps under increasing pressure: Operation “Signalgate” has reignited the debate around secure comms platforms, especially in high-risk sectors like journalism and government. More regulation might be coming our way, so watch this space.  🎯 TL;DR: Threat trends to brief your execs on You don’t need another list of vague “cyber trends.” You need the TL;DR that matters in the boardroom. Here’s a snapshot of what topics you might want to add to your deck this month: Zero Trust isn’t theory anymore. It’s become the bare minimum expectation. Especially as multi-cloud sprawl grows and identity-based attacks continue to rise.  Quantum risk is becoming real. NIST’s push for post-quantum cryptography standards is no longer just academic—it’s your five-year plan. It’s time to get quantum-ready. Security teams are (still) under-resourced. And threat actors know it. The burnout is real. The workload is huge. The answer? Skills benchmarking and hands-on training that actually reflects what your teams face in the wild. 👉 Share your win with the community Your expertise and insights are invaluable. And we’re eager to share them with our vast audience of over 3 million members. We’d be honored to feature your top "win" of the month related to your team, department, or security program in the next edition of ThreatReady. A “win” could be: Achieving compliance or industry standards. Successfully onboarding new team members. Celebrating your team’s performance. The top wins will be shared in next month’s edition of ThreatReady (and if it’s really good, it may get some additional love on social media). Want to share your win? Subject: The Future of Tech Needs You! Cisco Learn-a-Thon
Body: The Future of Tech Needs You! Join the International Girls in ICT Day Learn-A-Thon! Technology is shaping every industry, creating millions of new job opportunities—but women are still vastly underrepresented in tech. With only 29.2% of the STEM workforce being female, we cannot afford to leave women behind. Diversity fuels innovation, and closing the gender gap is the only way forward.   That’s why Cisco Networking Academy is launching the International Girls in ICT Day Learn-A-Thon—an opportunity to gain essential tech skills, explore future careers, and take your first step into the world of technology. No matter your background, tech has a place for you!   Choose from three exciting courses and start learning today:   Introduction to Cybersecurity – Discover how to protect digital landscapes in today’s connected world. Enroll now   Introduction to Data Science – Learn how to uncover insights from data and make informed decisions. Enroll now   Introduction to Modern AI – Explore the power of artificial intelligence and its role in shaping the future. Enroll now   Don’t miss this chance to gain valuable skills and be part of the next generation of female tech leaders!The future of tech needs your voice, talent, and ideas. Let’s break barriers together! The future is here. Don’t miss this chance to discover how you can kick-start your career in the exciting world of technology!   <[[${FacebookLink}]]>  <[[${YoutubeLink}]]>  <[[${TwitterLink}]]>  <[[${LinkedInLink}]]>   Join our feeds to be the first to hear about updates and opportunities, and share your own innovative ideas.  Please do not reply to this email.   To unsubscribe, log in to Cisco Networking Academy , click on your name (top right corner), and update your Notification and Email Preferences. If you are no longer part of the Networking Academy program and need to have your account deleted, log in, go to help, and submit a request for deletion. If you do not have a Cisco Networking Academy account, unsubscribe here .  © 2021 Cisco Systems, Inc. and/or its affiliates. All rights reserved. 170 W Tasman, San Jose, CA 95134. Body: Read the latest from Malwarebytes Labs Read the latest from Malwarebytes Labs     View in browser      NEWSLETTER     NEWSLETTER           BIG NEWS    All Gmail users at risk from clever replay attack    All Gmail users at risk from clever replay attack   All Google accounts could end up compromised by a clever replay attack on  Gmail users that abuses Google infrastructure.       Zoom attack tricks victims into allowing remote access to install malware and  steal money    Zoom attack tricks victims into allowing remote access to install malware and  steal money   Attackers are luring victims into a Zoom call and then taking over their PC to  install malware, infiltrate their accounts, and steal their assets.       Shopify faces privacy lawsuit for collecting customer data     Shopify faces privacy lawsuit for collecting customer data    Shopify is facing a class action lawsuit that could change the way globally  active companies can be held accountable for use of customer data.       4.7 million customers’ data accidentally leaked to Google by Blue Shield of  California    4.7 million customers’ data accidentally leaked to Google by Blue Shield of  California   Blue Shield of California says it accidentally leaked the personal data of 4.7  million individuals to Google after a Google Analytics misconfiguration. Subject: Educational Codeforces Round 178 (Rated for Div. 2)
Body: Hello, Jayceee1.  The series of Educational Rounds continues thanks to the support of the Neapolis University Pafos. They offer a BSc in Computer Science and Artificial Intelligence. The JetBrains Foundation supports this bachelor's program and offers 20 fully funded scholarships for talented first-year students, along with 2 additional scholarships for students wishing to transfer into the second year of the program. Learn more.  You are welcome to register and compete in Educational Codeforces Round 178. he round is partially based on the Saratov Multi-University Olympiad and the Nizhny Novgorod Regional Collegiate Olympiad It starts on Monday, April, 28, 2025 14:35 (UTC). The contest duration is 2 hours.  Register Now → The round will be rated for ratings up to 2100.  The goal of educational rounds is to practice and educate, rather than to compete. You can read the details in this post dedicated to them. In short:  * Not only problems, but also exercises can be used. * Useful ideas will be reused to introduce them to a wider range of participants, even if they are well-known. * Often the formal text of the statements. * Rated for Div. 2, unrated for Div. 1. * ICPC rules + 12-hour open hacking phase.  The allowed programming languages are C/C++, Pascal, Java, C#, Python, Ruby, Perl, PHP, Haskell, Scala, OCaml, Go, D, JavaScript, Rust and Kotlin.  The round will be held on the rules of Educational Rounds, so read the rules (here) beforehand. The round will be for newcomers and participants from both divisions. But the difficulty of problems is for Div 2. Want to compete? Do not forget to register for the contest and check your handle on the registrants page. The registration will be open for the whole contest duration.  If you have any questions, please feel free to ask me on the pages of Codeforces. If you no longer wish to receive these emails, click https://codeforces.com/unsubscribe/contests/51474b72d79ac8ec8363936f1ca54cbe6dbb957a/ to unsubscribe.  Wish you high rating, MikeMirzayanov and Codeforces team

Subject: Codeforces Round 1021
Body: Attention! The round starts on Saturday, April, 26, 2025 08:35 (UTC).  Hello, Jayceee1.  I'm glad to invite you to take part in Codeforces Round 1021. Actually it will be two separate rounds "Codeforces Round #1021 (Div. 1)" and "Codeforces Round #1021 (Div. 2)". The division problemsets will share many problems, but not all of them will be the same. So, Div. 1 users should register on "Codeforces Round #1021 (Div. 1)" while Div. 2 users should register on "Codeforces Round #1021 (Div. 2)". It starts on Saturday, April, 26, 2025 08:35 (UTC). The contest duration is 2 hours 30 minutes. The allowed programming languages are C/C++, Pascal, Java, C#, Python, Ruby, Perl, PHP, Haskell, Scala, OCaml, Go, D, JavaScript, Rust and Kotlin.  Register Now →  Problems are prepared by FairyWinx, I_love_kirill22, I_love_teraqqq and wilcot. Don't miss the round!  The round will be held on the rules of Codeforces, so read the rules (here and here) beforehand. The round will be for newcomers and participants from the both divisions. Want to compete? Do not forget to register for the contest and check your handle on the registrants page. The registration will be closed 5 minutes before the contest.  If you have any questions, please feel free to ask me on the pages of Codeforces. If you no longer wish to receive these emails, click https://codeforces.com/unsubscribe/contests/51474b72d79ac8ec8363936f1ca54cbe6dbb957a/ to unsubscribe.  Wish you high rating, MikeMirzayanov and Codeforces team

Subject: [Dreamhack] 🎫 ticket On Sale NOW: LIVE Dreamhack CTF tickets!
Body: Dreamhack CTF Season 7 #8        Hello Jaycelation,  Greetings from Dreamhack, the hacker’s playground.  As the gentle breeze of spring fills the air, we hope you're soaking up every moment of this short but sweet season—and that a little warmth is blooming in your everyday life too!      Hacking Live!  Get ready! Dreamhack CTF Season 7 Round 8 is happening this Saturday, April 26th - don’t miss the thrill!  Come enjoy the CTF Live with Amo, Boko, and Nando!    We'll randomly select four more lucky participants (solve at least one challenge to enter) to receive their very own. Don’t miss your chance to score exclusive merch from B.A.N.—Dreamhack’s hottest new hacking idols!   * 🗓️ Schedule   * 2025/4/26 09:00 ~ 23:59 (15hrs, UTC+9)    * ☘️ Eligibility   * Up to Dreamhack Gold II 1699    * Players outside this tier range are welcome to join, but please note that  their results will not be reflected on the leaderboard nor impact the  rating.    * ❓ Challenge Categories   * Pwnable, Reversing, Web, Crypto    * ☂️ Prizes   * Dreamhack Umbrellas   * 1 CTF Winner    * 4 Lucky Draws (Min. 1 solve required!)    * Prize draws will be held at the #dh-ctf-season7 channel in the   [Dreamhack  Official Discord server]  https://discord.gg/dreamhackio   .   We can’t wait to see you all in action!  Happy Hacking!  - The Dreamhack Team    [Click to Participate] https://dreamhack.io/ctf/662  This email was sent to all Dreamhack members. Subject: New UI, new models: Gemini 2.5 Flash, Veo 2, Starter Apps, and more
Body: Email not displaying correctly? View it online  Browsing Gemini Templates     Introducing Gemini 2.5 Flash, Veo 2, new Starter Apps, and more  A revamped UI to streamline building with the Gemini API just landed,   including a more intuitive prompting experience and dashboard to access API   keys! Here’s what else is new:  - Thinking with Gemini 2.5 Flash      and 2.5 Pro   :   Get insight into how reasoning models “think” in AI Studio. - Video generation   :   Start prototyping apps with Veo 2, now available in the API. - New Starter Apps   :   Customize using the built-in code editor, then save, share, and integrate   the code in your projects. - Real-time streaming   :   Explore how the Live API enables voice and video bidirectional streaming   for chat applications, transcription, and more.  Build with Gemini 2.5 Flash     Gemini 2.5 thinking     Start building with Gemini 2.5 Flash  Gemini 2.5 Flash      is our first hybrid reasoning model, giving you the ability to turn   thinking on or off, or to specify thinking budgets to find the right   trade-off between quality, cost, and latency.  Try Gemini 2.5 Flash     Generate Videos with Veo     Create high-quality videos with Veo 2  Learn how to turn text, images, or both into video using Veo 2   ,   Google’s state-of-the-art video generation model that can capture a wide   spectrum of visual styles and simulate real-world physics.  Generate Video with Veo 2     Talk to Gemini Live     Try real-time interactions with the Live API  The Live API      has added much-requested features to build apps, including support for 30   languages, text streaming, configurable Voice Activity Detection (VAD), and   much more. Now in preview.  Stream the Live API     Starter App Gallery     Explore a new Starter App gallery  Get inspired      with new interactive examples you can use, learn from, fork, and share,   like the Gemini 95 demo that pays homage to a retro operating system,   vibe-coded with Gemini 2.5 Pro.  Try the Gemini 95 demo     Resources  - Learn how thinking in Gemini 2.5 works in docs   . - Get ready to build apps with pricing      for Gemini 2.5 models. 2.5 Pro now supports context caching for lower costs   on recurring input tokens. - Find new starter notebooks for the Live API, Veo 2, and more in the   Cookbook   .  We’re working to get developers helpful tools to accelerate Gemini API   development and release production-ready capabilities even faster. Building   your own app? Get support on the developer forum   .  Thank you,  Your Google AI Studio team  Create prompt     Starter apps     Documentation     Ask questions in the developer forum     © 2025 Google LLC 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA 94043  This email was sent to jaycedang0601@gmail.com because you signed up to   receive emails about Google AI. If you do not wish to receive these emails,   please unsubscribe   .

Subject: Create images with GPT image generation on Poe
Body: Hi everyone,  GPT image generation, first introduced in ChatGPT last month, is live on Poe! You can use it directly within GPT-4o (https://poe.com/GPT-4o), and it's the new default image model for subscribers when they use Assistant (https://poe.com/assistant).  One of the best image models to date, it excels at understanding prompts to match your vision, offers sharp and accurate text renderings (great for posters, cards, and memes), and is exceptional at restyling photos.  Unique features to try it with on Poe: - '/repeat' generates multiple versions at once (up to 10) - Send new requests even while the previous image is generating - Combine it with a video model (e.g., Kling or Veo 2) to bring images to life  Poe Apps and bots: - Make incredible image-based Poe Apps by using the standalone GPT-Image-1 bot with App Creator (https://poe.com/App-Creator) (no coding skills required) - Put your own spin on existing Poe Apps through our new Remix feature (try your own take on a retro throwback: https://poe.com/Yearbookify) - Use it as a base model for your prompt and server bots  To get started, try GPT-4o here (https://poe.com/GPT-4o) or on any platform where you use Poe. We're looking forward to seeing what you create!  To stay informed on our latest updates and announcements, you can follow us on X (https://twitter.com/poe_platform) or join our Discord server (https://discord.com/invite/joinpoe).  Thanks, The Poe Team

Subject: Find up to 1000 subdomains for free
Just Hacking Training - Platform Update and 15% Off Everything
Body: **You Passed Security+… Great! Tick that HR box.** **But can you pass a technical interview?**  🆓 Free Preview! 🆓  We've released three free lessons from the newly updated [Constructing Defense Path (2025 Edition)](https://www.justhacking.com/course/constructing-defense/) now with Splunk. With its massive hands-on lab and 100+ videos, see for yourself why **John Hammond** praises ConDef as "one of the flagship ways to start a career in cybersecurity."  At only $400 until April 30, it’s a fraction of the cost of other cyber ranges, yet much more in-depth. Get ready to perform attacks and see what happens from a defensive perspective. **Learn. Attack. Defend. Repeat!**  Try ConDef Free Now! (https://www.justhacking.com/course/constructing-defense/)  “**Additional 15% Off EVERYTHING!**  Use code **TaxDay15 **for 15% off all training on JHT. Yes… that includes already discounted courses and bundles!  Expires Midnight ET on April 30“ —   ## **Platform Updates**  * **Recently Released **[**Bundles**](https://learn.justhacking.com/catalog)**:**    * The “Mishaal” Bundle – All of Mishaal Khan’s Training for only $150!  * Mastering Active Directory Security (MADS) Volumes 1–3 = 20% Off  * Windows Malware Dev (WMD) 1–3 = 20% Off  * **Additional Releases this Month:**    * [Name Your Price Hack-Along - M!$#'s geoINT Challenge](https://www.justhacking.com/hackalong/hal-ms-geoint-challenge-2/) by Mishaal Khan  * [Free UC - Phishing](https://www.justhacking.com/uc/uc-phishing/) by Cori Macy  * [Free UC - Windows Internals](https://www.justhacking.com/uc/uc-windows-internals/) by Shikata  * [Free UC - Windows Administration](https://www.justhacking.com/uc/uc-windows-administration/) by Patrick Gorman  * [Free UC - Threat Landscape Reports (TLRs)](https://www.justhacking.com/uc/uc-threat-landscape-reports-tlrs/) by Jennifer Funk  * [CTF – Huntress 2023](https://www.justhacking.com/ctf/ctf-huntress-2023/)  * **Cons & JHT Livestreams** with John Hammond Twice a Month – Details on our [Events Page](https://www.justhacking.com/events/):    * May 1 (tentatively) Mishaal Khan Launches Next Level OSINT Course  * May 23 with Ellie Daw on Quantum Programming  * Get JHT stickers in the IoT Village at BSidesSF, RSA and HackSpaceCon!  * **Free Previews** – We just added a great new feature allowing you to take a **test drive of our courses**. ConDef is the first to get them; others coming soon! Details will be on each web page.  * **VPN Access** – We just launched the ability to have VPN access into our virtual lab environment. Now you have a choice to learn in a way that suits you best… web-based VMs or bring your own tools and go at it! We’ve already begun rolling this out to a few of our training options. Check each product page for updates.  * **Certificates of Completion** – Don’t forget to share your success on social media. **Tag JHT (**[LI](https://www.linkedin.com/company/justhacking/)**|**[X](https://x.com/justhackinghq)**)** so we can celebrate with you! You can even add our training to your LinkedIn profile and resumes.  * **Coming Soon:**    * Courses: Next Level OSINT, ConDef Lite, Phishing, MADS Vol 4, WMD Advanced  * [Upskill Challenges](https://www.justhacking.com/types/upskill-challenges/) to include topics on more API types, Brute Force Attacks, Shellcode, et al.  * [Hack-Alongs](https://www.justhacking.com/types/hack-alongs/) & [CTFs](https://www.justhacking.com/types/capture-the-flag/) for fun ways to get more hands-on activity.  Youtube: Just Hacking Training (JHT) (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=738tv2Q-aT0)  **Thanks for choosing us!** 🙏   We’re new and growing fast with 45+ training options, but we wouldn’t be here without you and the greater community.  With new training released twice a month throughout 2025, bi-monthly livestreams with JHT’s own John Hammond and our All-Stars, and even some “Name Your Price” options, JHT promises “Focused Technical Training for All Levels” regardless of experience or budget.  ---------- [Discord](https://jh.live/discord) | [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/company/justhacking/) | [Twitch](https://www.twitch.tv/johnhammond010) | [Twitter/X](https://x.com/justhackinghq) | [YouTube](https://www.youtube.com/@justhackingtraining)   ----------Forget all the noise and get to Just Hacking! ✌️  Thanks, The Just Hacking Training Team   ———  You are reading a plain text version of this post. Subject: We Are Live! Join Cisco's International Girls in ICT Day!
Body: We Are Live! We're thrilled to announce that International Girls in ICT Day presented by Cisco, is now live! Discover how to harness your unique strengths, build bridges where divides exist, and inspire others to follow in your footsteps.   Don't miss this chance to learn from top Cisco leaders. Together, let's shape a digital future that's inclusive for all! Remember to share your favorite moments. Engage with us by using the official event hashtag #FindYourself.   <[[${FacebookLink}]]>  <[[${YoutubeLink}]]>  <[[${TwitterLink}]]>  <[[${LinkedInLink}]]>   Join our feeds to be the first to hear about updates and opportunities, and share your own innovative ideas.  Please do not reply to this email.   To unsubscribe, log in to Cisco Networking Academy , click on your name (top right corner), and update your Notification and Email Preferences. If you are no longer part of the Networking Academy program and need to have your account deleted, log in, go to help, and submit a request for deletion. Subject: Codeforces Round 1020 (Div. 3)
Body: Hello, Jayceee1.  You are welcome to register and compete in Codeforces Round 1020 (Div. 3). It starts on Thursday, April, 24, 2025 14:35 (UTC). The contest duration is 2 hours 15 minutes. The allowed programming languages are C/C++, Pascal, Java, C#, Python, Ruby, Perl, PHP, Haskell, Scala, OCaml, Go, D, JavaScript, Rust and Kotlin.  Div. 3 rounds are designed especially for participants with a rating below 1600. We invite you to participate in the competition!  The goal of such rounds is to help beginner participants to gain skills and to get new knowledge in a real contest. You can read the details in this post dedicated to them. In short:  * Not only real problems, but also exercises can be used. * Our main goal is to give nice training problems, so we do not care much about the innovativeness of the problems. * Often the formal text of the statements. * Rated for participant with the rating below 1600. * ICPC rules + 12-hour open hacking phase. * Untrusted participants are not included in the official ranklist.  The round will be held on the rules of Educational Rounds, so read the rules (here) beforehand. The round will be for newcomers and participants with a rating below 1600. Want to compete? Do not forget to register for the contest and check your handle on the registrants page. The registration will be open for the whole contest duration.  If you have any questions, please feel free to ask me on the pages of Codeforces. If you no longer wish to receive these emails, click https://codeforces.com/unsubscribe/contests/51474b72d79ac8ec8363936f1ca54cbe6dbb957a/ to unsubscribe.  Wish you high rating, MikeMirzayanov and Codeforces team

Subject: Vietnam ICT Momentum: Strong Growth, Smart Partnerships, Bold Vision
Body: Vietnam Dynamic  By Thái Vân Linh   By Thái Vân Linh                Read this article on LinkedIn to join the conversation Read on LinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/comm/pulse/vietnam-ict-momentum-strong-growth-smart-partnerships-th%C3%A1i-v%C3%A2n-linh-vm6dc?lipi=urn%3Ali%3Apage%3Aemail_email_series_follow_newsletter_01%3BJ5GbkAKrRE2kGLC0unbiOg%3D%3D&midToken=AQEMCMuQJusoZg&midSig=19I_BDZ5-7TXI1&trk=eml-email_series_follow_newsletter_01-null-0-read_more_banner_cta_&trkEmail=eml-email_series_follow_newsletter_01-null-0-read_more_banner_cta_-null-i8mwdi~m9tec5cc~4t-null-null&eid=i8mwdi-m9tec5cc-4t&otpToken=MTMwNDFlZTIxYTI3Y2ZjMGJjMjgwZmViNDExYWUyYjc4N2NlZDI0Nzk5YWQ4YTZhN2JjZjA1NjY0OTVkNWJmMGYzZDZkN2U5NGFlY2NhZjA2YzgxY2E4NTJlZDE4NjA3NTY3YTJhZDZmZTYyYjhmMmFlZTAxNjE0LDEsMQ%3D%3D    TLDR: Vietnam’s ICT and electronics sectors posted strong performance in 2024, with ICT revenue reaching USD166.7 billion, electronics manufacturing expanding 8.3%, and electronics exports growing 16.9% year-on-year. Vietnam’s Information and Communication Technology (ICT) industry has become a vital driver of the country’s economic development. In 2024, total ICT revenue reached approximately USD166.7 billion, up 13.2% from 2023, contributing over USD4.4 billion to the national budget. The sector now accounts for 11.2% of GDP, supported by over 1.5 million workers and 54,500 digital tech enterprises. The government's "Make in Vietnam" strategy has accelerated the shift from low-value outsourcing to high-value domestic innovation, helping elevate the country’s global tech profile. 1. MANUFACTURING MOMENTUM AND EXPORT RECOVERY Vietnam’s electronics manufacturing sector grew by 8.3% in 2024, recovering from prior slowdowns. Key segments saw notable growth: consumer electronics (+16.1%), batteries and accumulators (+17.7%), and electrical equipment (+13.3%). Electronics exports surged by 16.8% to USD132.3 billion, while imports of components climbed to USD107 billion (+21.7%), with China, South Korea, and Taiwan as major suppliers. Backed by global players like Samsung, LG, Intel, and Foxconn, Vietnam’s manufacturing base is rapidly scaling up, with Samsung’s northern factories now producing nearly half of its global smartphones. The country is targeting USD160 billion in electronics exports by 2025. 2. DIGITAL INFRASTRUCTURE AND STRATEGIC PARTNERSHIPS Vietnam is advancing its digital economy through infrastructure upgrades and cross-border collaboration, particularly with Singapore. Joint initiatives include enhancing 5G connectivity, strengthening cybersecurity, and deploying AI in government and financial services. Projects such as submarine cables, modern data centers, and Security Operations Centers are improving digital resilience and service delivery. These partnerships are also helping Vietnam build e-Government platforms and expand digital payments, positioning the country for deeper integration into the global digital economy. 3. INNOVATION AND OUTLOOK FOR FUTURE Innovation remains central to Vietnam’s tech strategy. The digital technology sector generated USD155 billion in revenue in 2024, with domestic value-added contributions increasing to 31.8%, up from 21.4% in 2019. Approximately 1,500 Vietnamese ICT firms now generate international revenue. With strong startup activity and government support, the number of tech enterprises is projected to reach 60,000 by 2025. The government has set an ICT revenue target of USD172 billion for 2025, underscoring long-term confidence in digital growth. With increasing international cooperation, rising domestic value creation, and a growing tech workforce, Vietnam is well-positioned to lead Southeast Asia’s digital future and solidify its global competitiveness in the years ahead. Vietnam ICT Momentum: Strong Growth, Smart Partnerships, Bold Vision ===== TLDR: Ngành Công nghệ thông tin và truyền thông (ICT) và điện tử của Việt Nam đã đạt hiệu quả hoạt động mạnh mẽ trong năm 2024, với doanh thu đạt 166.7 tỷ USD, sản xuất điện tử tăng 8.3%, và xuất khẩu điện tử tăng 16.9% so với cùng kỳ năm trước. Ngành Công nghệ thông tin và truyền thông (ICT) của Việt Nam đã trở thành một động lực quan trọng thúc đẩy sự phát triển kinh tế của quốc gia. Năm 2024, tổng doanh thu ICT đạt khoảng 166.7 tỷ USD, tăng 13.2% so với năm 2023, đóng góp hơn 4.4 tỷ USD vào ngân sách quốc gia. Ngành này hiện chiếm 11.2% GDP, được hỗ trợ bởi hơn 1.5 triệu lao động và 54,500 doanh nghiệp công nghệ số. Chiến lược "Make in Vietnam" của Chính phủ đã thúc đẩy quá trình chuyển dịch từ gia công giá trị thấp sang đổi mới sáng tạo giá trị cao trong nước, góp phần nâng cao vị thế công nghệ toàn cầu của Việt Nam. 1. TĂNG TRƯỞNG SẢN XUẤT VÀ PHỤC HỒI XUẤT KHẨU Ngành sản xuất điện tử của Việt Nam đã tăng trưởng 8.3% trong năm 2024, phục hồi sau giai đoạn chững lại trước đó. Một số phân khúc chủ chốt ghi nhận mức tăng đáng kể: điện tử tiêu dùng (+16.1%), pin và ắc quy (+17.7%), và thiết bị điện (+13.3%). Xuất khẩu điện tử tăng mạnh 16.8%, đạt 132.3 tỷ USD, trong khi nhập khẩu linh kiện điện tử tăng lên 107 tỷ USD (+21.7%). Trung Quốc, Hàn Quốc và Đài Loan hiện đang là các nhà cung cấp chính. Được hậu thuẫn bởi các tập đoàn toàn cầu như Samsung, LG, Intel và Foxconn, sản xuất của Việt Nam đang mở rộng quy mô nhanh chóng, với các nhà phía bắc của Samsung hiện đang sản xuất gần một nửa tổng số điện thoại thông minh toàn cầu của hãng. Việt Nam đặt mục tiêu đạt 160 tỷ USD trong xuất khẩu điện tử vào năm 2025. 2. CƠ SỞ HẠ TẦNG SỐ VÀ CÁC ĐỐI TÁC CHIẾN LƯỢC Việt Nam đang thúc đẩy nền kinh tế số thông qua việc nâng cấp cơ sở hạ tầng và hợp tác quốc tế, đặc biệt với Singapore. Các sáng kiến hợp tác bao gồm: nâng cao kết nối 5G, tăng cường an ninh mạng, và ứng dụng trí tuệ nhân tạo (AI) trong Chính phủ và các dịch vụ tài chính. Các dự án như cáp ngầm, trung tâm dữ liệu hiện đại, và trung tâm điều hành an ninh mạng, đang góp phần cải thiện khả năng phục hồi số và nâng cao chất lượng cung cấp dịch vụ. Các mối quan hệ đối tác này cũng hỗ trợ Việt Nam xây dựng các nền tảng Chính phủ điện tử (e-Government) và mở rộng hệ thống thanh toán số, tạo tiền đề để hội nhập sâu hơn vào nền kinh tế số toàn cầu. 3. ĐỔI MỚI SÁNG TẠO VÀ TRIỂN VỌNG TƯƠNG LAI Đổi mới sáng tạo tiếp tục là trọng tâm trong chiến lược công nghệ của Việt Nam. Ngành công nghệ số tạo ra doanh thu 155 tỷ USD vào năm 2024, với tỷ lệ giá trị gia tăng trong nước đạt 31.8%, tăng mạnh so với mức 21.4% vào năm 2019. Hiện có khoảng 1,500 doanh nghiệp ICT Việt Nam tạo ra doanh thu từ thị trường quốc tế. Với hoạt động khởi nghiệp sôi động và sự hỗ trợ từ Chính phủ, số lượng doanh nghiệp công nghệ được kỳ vọng sẽ đạt 60,000 vào năm 2025. Chính phủ đã đặt mục tiêu doanh thu ngành ICT đạt 172 tỷ USD vào năm 2025, thể hiện niềm tin dài hạn vào sự tăng trưởng của nền kinh tế số. Với việc thúc đẩy hợp tác quốc tế, gia tăng giá trị nội địa, và lực lượng lao động công nghệ ngày càng lớn mạnh, Việt Nam đang ở vị thế thuận lợi để dẫn đầu tương lai số của khu vực Đông Nam Á và củng cố năng lực cạnh tranh toàn cầu trong những năm tới. === Link to research Vietnam’s ICT industry makes global waves with "Make in Vietnam" strategy Ngành ICT Việt Nam 2024: Tăng trưởng mạnh mẽ, khẳng định vị thế dẫn đầu - Subject: Issue 274: Automated for the people
Body: Agentic AI, freezing funds, and TLS certificate changes ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌          23 April    Every other week, it seems like somebody has a new AI-related take or  buzzword, and the rest of us have to sort out whether it's worth learning  about. Like agents; what the heck are they? Fortunately, we dug into that very  question to see what lies beneath the hype. Agents, like a lot of software,  help automate tasks—we're got a look at how much you can automate sysadmin  tasks. Then, with all these AI agents running rampant in your system, you need  to think about scale—in our latest Leaders of Code, Recursion's VP of  engineering Maureen Makes does just that.  As we've often promised and occasionally delivered, we have more for you  besides AI. In the latest We'll Be In Touch, Kyle sits down with former Stacker  Michael Stum to chat about WebAssembly, how he learned to code by tackling  Stack Overflow questions, and more. Speaking of Stack Overflow (aren't we  always?), our private version, Stack Overflow for Teams, has a new release for  Enterprise users.  Okay readers, lightning round . How do you tell HR that you're  quitting because your desk is terrible? Why does Discord see through time? What  can you learn from the failure of a startup? Will the CVE database disappear  when its grants run out? Whew!     From the blog   Wait, what is agentic AI?   stackoverflow.blog Is “agentic AI” just a buzzword, or is it the sea change it seems?  Engineering teams need to adapt to AI’s scaling challenges   stackoverflow.blog AI is not a linear process. To scale effectively, engineering leaders must  account for varied edge cases, presenting a new set of challenges.  WBIT #7: Exploring WebAssembly with the first SO user to get 10k rep   stackoverflow.blog Kyle interviews Michael Stum, a former Stacker who started (and returned) to  answering questions on the community site.  Smarter insights, stronger teams: New features for Stack Overflow for Teams   stackoverflow.blog 2025.3 | Teams Enterprise Release  Like self-driving cars, fully AI-automated sysadmins don’t exist   stackoverflow.blog As with cars, there are few system administration tasks that involve little to  no automation.     Interesting questions   Discord thinks I am living in the future - why?   superuser.com The Back to the Future reboot looks pretty boring.  I’ve decided to leave my job entirely over ergonomic reasons. How honest  should I be at the exit interview?   workplace.stackexchange.com “You're not leaving over an ergonomic issue, you're leaving over their  continued refusal to address your very reasonable concerns regarding your  working environment and its effects on your health. ”  My quadriplegic relative would like to fly long distance. He has a full time  aide and will require a lie-down seat. Are aides allowed by airlines?   travel.stackexchange.com “It’s important to be as specific and detailed about your requirements as  possible.”  What gives the executive branch the power to freeze a college’s funding?   politics.stackexchange.com Just another reason to read every clause in every contract.     Links from around the web   Postmortem for a startup  buildwithtract.com If you want to succeed, read about failure.  The four kinds of optimization   tratt.net If you look hard enough, you may find a fifth kind.  CISA extends funding to ensure ‘no lapse in critical CVE services’   www.bleepingcomputer.com The latest in a wild ride: funding cut, new foundation to take over, funding  renewed so there's no downtime.  TLS certificate lifetimes will officially reduce to 47 days   www.digicert.com Over the next four years, you'll need some sort of automation to manage your  TLS certificates.   Onboard, organize, and bring your team up to speed in a jiffy. Try Stack  Overflow for Teams   .
