Subject: NetAcad Student Newsletter – April 2025
Body: Hello Jayce,    The new experience at NetAcad.com is live! We're excited to see that many classes are already underway. This milestone marks a significant step in our mission to power an inclusive future for all. In our ongoing spirit of innovation, we will continue to add more teaching and learning features, courses, and resources.   To our partners and educators: thank you for your continued support, patience, and trust in Cisco Networking Academy. We highly value your collaboration and look forward to the positive impact we will continue to make together in our communities around the world.   Scroll down for tips on the new NetAcad.com platform, new courses, orientation learning collections, and more. We are also thrilled to unveil a whole new page dedicated to careers promoting current job opportunities with new employment partners like Indeed, the #1 job search platform (currently U.S. only).   And with Cybersecurity Awareness Month fast-approaching, you can get ready by checking out the first in our 10-part virtual series (see the Events section)! We also have a campaign  Sourcebook forthcoming, so be on the lookout for this awesome guide that will help you and your instructors promote opportunities and attract even more students. Finally, don't forget to remind your instructors to encourage their students to check out the new Find yourself in the future and Women Rock-IT special events coming soon. First report released The AI-Enabled ICT Workforce Consortium - led by Cisco with 8 leading tech companies plus key advisors - releases first report. Looks at effects of AI on top 50 ICT jobs, with actionable training recommendations to enable an AI-powered workforce. Update to legal agreements - August 26 Stay tuned for updates to The Cisco Networking Academy membership guide, Terms and Conditions, privacy documents, and Packet Tracer Distribution Terms on August 26. End-of-life: Continuing Education (CE) credits Cisco Networking Academy is exiting the Cisco Continuing Education (CE) Credits program. Learn more  Journey to Convergence Visit Convergence Hub Keep track of everything to do with Convergence of SkillsForAll.com and NetAcad.com on the Convergence Hub. FINAL CHECKLIST Convergence this month! Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet 1. Downtime: 72 hours Both NetAcad.com and SkillsForAll.com will be down for 72 hours. Start and end times depend on your location.  Take note  2. Maintain downtime access to Cisco Packet Tracer during planned downtime, especially for the 72 hours both sites will be down for convergence.  Prepare  Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet 3. Quick Start Guide Download the new NetAcad.com Quick Start Guide for Instructors. Download  4. Understand simplified roles See how the number of roles are simplifying in the new NetAcad.com.  View  Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet 5. Start course customizations now  IPD Course Customization recordings cover how to migrate course customizations to the new NetAcad.com. And you don't need to wait for convergence! Start building content now then add to courses from August 26.  Replay IPD  6. Are you ready for the new NetAcad.com? Three August IPD sessions continue preparing educators for convergence:  1) Top 5 Instructor Tasks 2) Academy Management 3) Are you Ready – convergence overview.  Register IPD  Course Updates Course translations Arabic and Ukrainian Networking course translations are now available as instructor-led. CCNP end-of-life End-of-life date has been set for Cisco Networking Academy CCNP Enterprise: Core Networking (ENCOR) and CCNP Enterprise: Advanced Routing and Services (ENARSI). Good News International Day of the World's Indigenous People August 8 marks International Day of the World's Indigenous People. Learn how our Cisco Networking Academy community elevates through education with these great success stories.   Julio Lezcano, Panama   I  Dr Gabriella Arellano, United States   I  Tully, Australia  Find yourself in the future Grow student numbers by promoting these quarterly virtual broadcasts as students navigate their own career path. Students learn latest technology trends, presented by Cisco experts. Coming soon: educator sourcebook.   <[[${FacebookLink}]]>  <[[${YoutubeLink}]]>  <[[${TwitterLink}]]>  <[[${LinkedInLink}]]>   Join our feeds to be the first to hear about updates and opportunities, and share your own innovative ideas.  Please do not reply to this email.   To unsubscribe, log in to Cisco Networking Academy , click on your name (top right corner), and update your Notification and Email Preferences. If you are no longer part of the Networking Academy program and need to have your account deleted, log in, go to help, and submit a request for deletion. Subject: Boost Your Career: CCNA Insights, Cisco Talos Strategies & Empowering Women in ICT
Body: Explore the transformative power of the CCNA certification with our new video, "A Glimpse at Your Future with the CCNA." Discover how becoming a Cisco Certified Network Associate can elevate your career, hear inspiring success stories, and gain expert exam preparation tips—all at your convenience. Don't miss this opportunity to enhance your networking career. Click below to start watching now! Hear From Cisco Top Female Leaders In honour of International Girls in ICT Day (April 24, 2025), Cisco is hosting an event focused on empowering girls of every background. This year's theme is celebrating the power of standing out to drive change. Discover Cisco Talos There are so many niche fields within cybersecurity, each dedicated to protecting infrastructures across the globe - and you're going to get the chance to explore several of them with our speaker Joe Marshall, Senior Security Strategist at Cisco Talos.   <[[${FacebookLink}]]>  <[[${YoutubeLink}]]>  <[[${TwitterLink}]]>  <[[${LinkedInLink}]]>   Join our feeds to be the first to hear about updates and opportunities, and share your own innovative ideas. Subject: Hi, robot: Half of all internet traffic now automated
Body: Read the latest from Malwarebytes Labs Read the latest from Malwarebytes Labs     View in browser      NEWSLETTER     NEWSLETTER           BIG NEWS    Hi, robot: Half of all internet traffic now automated     Hi, robot: Half of all internet traffic now automated    Bots now account for half of all internet traffic, according to a new study  that shows how non-human activity has grown online.       “I sent you an email from your email account,” sextortion scam claims     “I sent you an email from your email account,” sextortion scam claims    A new variant of the hello pervert emails claims that the target's system is  infected with a trojan and spoofs the victim’s email address.       Meta slurps up EU user data for AI training    Meta slurps up EU user data for AI training   Facebook parent company Meta has announced that European users will have their  public posts collected and used for AI training.       Hertz data breach caused by CL0P ransomware attack on vendor     Hertz data breach caused by CL0P ransomware attack on vendor    Car rental giant Hertz experienced a data breach due to a CL0P ransomware  attack on their file sharing vendor Cleo.          IS YOUR PHONE LISTENING TO YOU?   In this week’s Lock and Code podcast, host David Ruiz speaks with Electronic  Frontier Foundation Staff Technologist Lena Cohen about what we all want to  know: Are our phones really listening to us in order to deliver tailored ads? Subject: Codeforces Round 1019 (Div. 2)
Body: Hello, Jayceee1. Welcome to the regular Codeforces round.  I'm glad to invite you to take part in Codeforces Round 1019 (Div. 2). It starts on Monday, April, 21, 2025 14:35 (UTC). The contest duration is 2 hours. The allowed programming languages are C/C++, Pascal, Perl, Java, C#, Python (2 and 3), Ruby, PHP, Haskell, Scala, OCaml, D, Go, JavaScript and Kotlin.  Problems are prepared by NemanjaSo2005 and Blagoj. Don't miss the round!  The round will be held on the rules of Codeforces, so read the rules (here and here) beforehand.  It will be for newcomers or participants from the second division (non-rated users or those having less than 2100 rating points). Want to compete? Do not forget to register for the contest and check your handle on the registrants page. The registration will be closed 5 minutes before the contest.  Register Now →  If you have any questions, please feel free to ask me on the pages of Codeforces. If you no longer wish to receive these emails, click https://codeforces.com/unsubscribe/contests/51474b72d79ac8ec8363936f1ca54cbe6dbb957a/ to unsubscribe.  Wish you high rating, MikeMirzayanov and Codeforces team

Subject: Tact Smart Battle 1 (open for everybody, prizes)
Body: Attention! Unusual start time: the round starts on Monday, April, 21, 2025 09:00 (UTC).  Hello, Jayceee1. Welcome to the Tact Smart Battle 1, a smart contract coding competition powered by the Tact language, organized by TON Studio!  We invite you to register and compete in Tact Smart Battle 1. It starts on Monday, April, 21, 2025 09:00 (UTC). The contest duration is 1 week. This round is unrated for all participants.  Are you registered? If not, click here to register for this exciting challenge!  REGISTER   Participants will solve five progressively complex tasks focused on building efficient voting systems. Each task is crafted to test different aspects of smart contract development:  * Simple Voting: — basic voting system; * Serial Voting: — multiple proposals via a master contract; * Scalable Voting: — support up to 4 billion voters; * Voting with Refunds: — refunds to voters; * Gas-Managed Voting: — fully optimized contracts.  Everybody is welcome to participate. This is an individual competition.  Prizes:  * The $20,000 prize pool (in Toncoin) will be shared by the top 128 participants based on contest rankings. * All participants who submit valid solutions will receive a Soulbound Token (SBT), a non-transferrable token that highlights your contribution on-chain. * Top performers will earn exclusive SBTs to showcase their achievements.  Outstanding contestants may also receive interview invitations from TON Studio for career opportunities in blockchain development.  For questions or technical assistance, visit the official Telegram chat.  If you no longer wish to receive these emails, click https://codeforces.com/unsubscribe/contests/51474b72d79ac8ec8363936f1ca54cbe6dbb957a/ to unsubscribe.  Good luck! MikeMirzayanov and Codeforces team

Subject: Neowise Labs Contest 1 (Codeforces Round 1018, Div. 1 + Div. 2) (Rated for Everybody, prizes!)
Body: Attention! The round starts on Saturday, April, 19, 2025 14:35 (UTC).  Hello, Jayceee1.  I'm glad to invite you to take part in Neowise Labs Contest 1 (Codeforces Round 1018, Div. 1 + Div. 2). It will be a joint round for Div.1 and Div.2 participants. The round will be rated for all participants. The contest duration is 2 hours. The allowed programming languages are C/C++, Pascal, Java, C#, Python, Ruby, Perl, PHP, Haskell, Scala, OCaml, Go, D, JavaScript, Rust and Kotlin.  Neowise Labs is a proprietary trading firm. Most team members in Neowise Labs have maths and programming olympiad backgrounds. You can read more about Neowise Labs in here. If you want to join the Neowise Labs, fill out this form.  Register Now →  The round writers are thenymphsofdelphi and SanguineChameleon. Don't miss the round!  Participants will have a chance to win awesome prizes:  * Top three winners will receive Apple Macbook Air M4 13'; * The top 50 and random 50 participants from the top 500 will receive Neowise Labs caps; * …and other valuable presents!  The round will be held on the rules of Codeforces, so read the rules (here and here) beforehand. The round will be for newcomers and participants from the both divisions. Want to compete? Do not forget to register for the contest and check your handle on the registrants page. The registration will be closed 5 minutes before the contest.  If you have any questions, please feel free to ask me on the pages of Codeforces. If you no longer wish to receive these emails, click https://codeforces.com/unsubscribe/contests/51474b72d79ac8ec8363936f1ca54cbe6dbb957a/ to unsubscribe.  Wish you high rating, MikeMirzayanov and Codeforces team

Subject: ⚡ The Byte Is In: New Bootcamp, Threats Module, Azure, and more!
Body: TryHackMe ( https://tryhackme.com/hacktivities?utm_source=cio&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=byte )Unlock cutting-edge training & insights  Continue Learning ( https://tryhackme.com/hacktivities?utm_source=cio&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=byte )  ( https://tryhackme.zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_PiqFYiHvSa2DdHS72Vh2hg )  ************************** Master Microsoft Defender: Azure Bootcamp 101 **************************  Join this 45-minute live bootcamp run by one of our Azure experts, to walk through real-world attack scenarios using Microsoft Defender XDR.  You'll explore how to detect, investigate, and respond to threats across the kill chain using the same tools defenders use in the field.  We recommend having the TryHackMe Azure add-on ( https://tryhackme.com/cloud-access?utm_source=cio&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=byte ) for this session.     Seats are limited, so claim yours now!  Register Now ( https://tryhackme.zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_PiqFYiHvSa2DdHS72Vh2hg ) Here's this week's pop quiz:  Which Azure service helps detect and respond to threats across cloud and on-premises environments?  * Azure Monitor * Azure Security Center * Azure Blob Storage Find the correct answer at the bottom of the newsletter 👀     ********************************************* Did you know we have a Recent Threats Module? *********************************************  Learn about the latest industry threats. Get hands-on experience identifying, exploiting, and mitigating critical vulnerabilities.  Check Out The Module ( https://tryhackme.com/module/recent-threats?utm_source=cio&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=byte_beg )( https://tryhackme.com/module/recent-threats?utm_source=cio&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=byte_beg )  We want to congratulate some more users who are now SAL1 certified ( https://tryhackme.com/certification/security-analyst-level-1?utm_source=cio&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=byte_beg ) 🏅  juhikamaraj  Shadowhats  brooksd0810  Here's a comment from Francois (Shadowhats): "Certifications with hands-on practice, in my opinion, are more satisfying than just answering questions!"     ********************************* This week's newest beginner rooms *********************************  ( https://tryhackme.com/room/socl1alertreporting?utm_source=cio&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=byte_beg ) SOC L1 Alert Reporting  Launch walkthrough ( https://tryhackme.com/room/socl1alertreporting?utm_source=cio&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=byte_beg )Learn how to properly report, escalate, and communicate about high-risk SOC alerts.  ( https://tryhackme.com/room/sentinelintroduction?utm_source=cio&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=byte_beg ) MS Sentinel: Introduction  Launch walkthrough ( https://tryhackme.com/room/sentinelintroduction?utm_source=cio&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=byte_beg )What is Microsoft Sentinel and how does it fit into the role of a Security Operations Analyst?  ( https://tryhackme.com/room/kqlkustointroduction?utm_source=cio&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=byte_beg ) KQL (Kusto): Introduction  Launch walkthrough ( https://tryhackme.com/room/kqlkustointroduction?utm_source=cio&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=byte_beg )This room introduces you to Kusto Query Language and provides an overview of Microsoft Sentinel.  Continue learning ( https://tryhackme.com/hacktivities?utm_source=cio&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=byte )   This newsletter was brought to you by the TryHackMe Marketing team.     That's all from us — thank you for reading!     Lorena Gallo  Lifecycle Marketing Manager  Lorena Gallo  Lifecycle Marketing Manager  📝 The quiz answer is b. Subject: Build faster, break less—Types in collections are here
Body: Plus, keep specs and docs in sync with Spec Hub           Hi B22DCAT251,     When your collections don’t include types or schemas, you’re stuck working on  assumptions—guessing what a request should look like, hoping the response  matches. Now there’s a better way. With new types in collections, you can  define structure right in your workflow and build with confidence.  What can types in collections do for you?   * Catch data mismatches early with built-in validation  * Define data models across requests  * Enhance docs with clear, structured data models It’s everything you already love about Postman, now with stronger structure  and smarter defaults—so you can build with more confidence, right out of the  box.    Working with specs too? Postman's new Spec Hub helps you design, document, and  sync everything in one place.  Learn more          FOLLOW US           201 Mission Street Suite 2375 San Francisco, CA 94105   © 2025 Postman, Inc. All rights reserved.    Click here to unsubscribe.

Subject: Tận hưởng 4 tháng dùng gói Spotify Premium với giá 59000₫.
Body: Spotify Premium https://www.spotify.com/purchase/offer/2025-q2globalcampaign-intro/?marketing-campaign-id=2025-q2&utm_source=spotify&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=2025_q2&splot=T1JS8ATaQW2gJhAe_LM7FQ Tận hưởng 4 tháng dùng gói Spotify Premium với giá 59000₫.   Tận hưởng mọi giai điệu phù hợp với tâm trạng của bạn. Tải nhạc giàu cảm xúc xuống trong 4 tháng dùng gói Premium với giá 59000₫.   Dùng 4 tháng với giá 59000₫ ( https://www.spotify.com/purchase/offer/2025-q2globalcampaign-intro/?marketing-campaign-id=2025-q2&utm_source=spotify&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=2025_q2&splot=T1JS8ATaQW2gJhAe_LM7FQ )   Chỉ áp dụng cho gói Individual. Sau đó là 59000₫/tháng. Có áp dụng điều khoản và điều kiện ( https://www.spotify.com/legal/premium-promotional-offer-terms/ ). Chỉ dành cho những người chưa dùng thử gói Premium. Ưu đãi kết thúc vào ngày 19/05/2025. Khi nhấp vào nút trên, bạn sẽ đăng nhập vào tài khoản Spotify của mình để chọn nhận ưu đãi này. Đừng chuyển tiếp email này cho bất kỳ ai không được phép truy cập vào tài khoản của bạn.    -------------  Mua Spotify cho:   * iPhone (https://itunes.apple.com/app/spotify-music/id324684580)   * iPad (https://itunes.apple.com/app/spotify-music/id324684580)   * Android (https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.spotify.music)   * Khác (https://www.spotify.com/download/)  Thư này đã được gửi tới jaycedang0601@gmail.com. Nếu không muốn nhận các email này từ Spotify trong tương lai, bạn có thể chỉnh sửa hồ sơ của mình (https://www.spotify.com/account/notifications) hoặc hủy đăng ký (https://www.spotify.com/account/unsubscribe?t=JcXJDYAgEADAVmyAhFXCUc4ii0EJiKCi1ftwPjPBSk1K3BY5p3j31kruhcoV3nNIuQX%2FsLr%2FZ%2B%2FpqAyTY%2FZMLlIdDBjkTlg9Si7QkAKtnABOXBkPiBpQCZr1Bw%3D%3D&a=unsubscribe)     * Điều khoản sử dụng https://www.spotify.com/legal/end-user-agreement/   * Chính sách quyền riêng tư https://www.spotify.com/legal/privacy-policy/   * Liên hệ với chúng tôi https://www.spotify.com/about-us/contact/   Spotify AB, Regeringsgatan 19, 111 53, Stockholm, Sweden

Subject: Join Us for International Girls in ICT Day – Register Now!
Body: Empowering Girls of Every Background International Girls in ICT Day is fast approaching, and we invite you to be part of this global movement dedicated to bridging the gender gap in technology.         On April 24, Cisco female leaders are sharing their personal journeys, mentorship experiences, and insights on the future of tech: including AI & inclusivity. Why Should You Attend - Engage with Visionary Speakers: Listen to inspiring talks from global female leaders in tech, who will share their unique journeys, challenges, and triumphs in the industry.    	- Gain Insights into the Future of Tech: Discover the latest trends in technology, including discussions on AI, cybersecurity, and inclusivity, providing you with valuable knowledge to stay ahead in the field.    	- Empower Yourself and Others: Be part of a transformative experience that not only empowers you but also contributes to closing the gender gap in tech, creating a more inclusive and diverse future for all. Meet the Speakers Jacqueline Guichelaar Senior Vice-President Cisco Customer Experience APJC Adele Trombetta Senior Vice-President Cisco Customer Experience EMEA Let's unite to bridge the gap and create a tech future where everyone belongs!   <[[${FacebookLink}]]>  <[[${YoutubeLink}]]>  <[[${TwitterLink}]]>  <[[${LinkedInLink}]]>   Join our feeds to be the first to hear about updates and opportunities, and share your own innovative ideas. Subject: Issue 273: Would you open source your AI?
Body: The costs of speed, reasons to leave, and Lisp ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌          16 April    No matter where in the world you live, this newsletter is hitting your inbox  free of tariffs. I mean, it's always free, and we've got some excellent  freebies for you. We dropped the results of our survey on open-source AI, and  it's got plenty of insights into how developers of all experience levels view  the rise of open-source LLMs like LLaMa and DeepSeek.  On the podcast side, we have two conversations recorded at the HumanX  conference and one new Leaders of Code episode. We chatted with Amr Awadallah,  CEO of Vectara, about how AI's going to give us that "I know kung fu" moment  sooner rather than later. We serve up a conversation with a repeat customer,  Tomasz Tunguz, about his theories (and his Theory Ventures) about the AI  landscape. In Leaders of Code, our own Ellen Brandenberger chats with Maureen  Makes, VP of Engineering at Recursion, about whether you can move too fast with  AI.  Did you know that the #! is called a shebang? Me either. Find out how it works  with the Linux kernel in our links section. Want to know how dang wrong Jules  Verne (and, frankly, everybody else in 1865) was about the Rocky Mountains?  Check our questions. Dear reader, there's even more, so I'll get out of the way  of your scroll wheel.     From the blog   Open-source AI: Are younger developers leading the way?   stackoverflow.blog In March, over 1,000 developers and technologists gave us insights into what  they think about open source and the role it plays with AI.  Bottom of the first: A veteran VC’s take on the AI landscape   stackoverflow.blog Ryan welcomes Tomasz Tunguz of Theory Ventures back to the podcast to talk  about the intersection of AI and venture capital, the implications of AI on the  labor market, and the future of AI applications.  “There is a real cost to moving fast”: Using AI to accelerate drug discovery   stackoverflow.blog On this episode of Leaders of Code, Maureen Makes, VP of Engineering at  Recursion, discusses AI's role in drug discovery, scaling and integration  challenges, and the importance of innovation in achieving the high standards  desired.  How do you fact-check an AI?   stackoverflow.blog Ryan chats with Amr Awadallah, founder and CEO of GenAI platform Vectara about  how retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) has advanced, why fact-checking and  accurate data are essential in building AI applications, and how Vectara’s  Mockingbird model seeks to minimize hallucinations.  Fix Legacy Code IRL: Code Remix Summit | May 12–14 | Miami   promotion Join engineers from Spotify, Morgan Stanley, Broadcom & more to see how dev  teams tackle large-scale refactoring at scale. For engineers, architects & tech  leads. Hosted by Moderne (creators of OpenRewrite) & NFJS. Sponsored by Snyk,  Azul & CodeGate. 50% off with code STACK50.     Interesting questions   Is this a polished enough answer to, “Why do you want to leave?”   workplace.stackexchange.com “Almost all you are doing is complaining.”  What causes THIS level of dry rot?   bicycles.stackexchange.com These bicycle tires were made in Finland and should be able to withstand a  measly Italian winter.  Did Jules Verne not know how high the Rockies are?   history.stackexchange.com In 1865, did anyone know how high the Rockies are?  Was refused US visa as a minor, but found out only after submitting new  tourist application a decade later   travel.stackexchange.com “Am I likely to be denied permanently on the basis of providing false  information, even if by accident?”     Links from around the web   Demystifying the #! (shebang): Kernel Adventures    crocidb.com This guide explains the whole shebang and how it works with the Linux kernel.  Why I program in Lisp   funcall.blogspot.com While Lisp might not be the most popular language overall, it is this  programmer's favorite.  AI Index 2025: State of AI in 10 Charts    hai.stanford.edu AI models are getting smaller, cheaper, and more problematic.  Fintech founder charged with fraud after ‘AI’ shopping app found to be powered  by humans in the Philippines   techcrunch.com The Mechanical Turk lives and it's doing your shopping. Subject: Codeforces Round 1017 (Div. 4)
Body: Attention! Unusual start time: the round starts on Sunday, April, 13, 2025 15:35 (UTC).  Hello, Jayceee1.  I'm glad to invite you to take part in Codeforces Round 1017 (Div. 4). It starts on Sunday, April, 13, 2025 15:35 (UTC). The contest duration is 2 hours 15 minutes. The allowed programming languages are C/C++, Pascal, Java, C#, Python, Ruby, Perl, PHP, Haskell, Scala, OCaml, Go, D, JavaScript, Rust and Kotlin.  Div. 4 rounds are designed for participants with the rating below 1400 (and for unrated participants/newcomers).  Register Now →  The format of the event will be identical to Div. 3 and Educational Rounds. In short:  * Not only real problems, but also exercises can be used. * Our main goal is to give nice training problems, so we do not care much about the innovativeness of the problems. * Often the formal text of the statements. * Rated for participant with the rating below 1400. * ICPC rules + 12-hour open hacking phase. * Untrusted participants are not included in the official ranklist.  The round will be rated for newcomers and participants with the rating below 1400. Want to compete? Do not forget to register for the contest and check your handle on the registrants page. The registration will be open for the whole contest duration.  If you have any questions, please feel free to ask me on the pages of Codeforces. If you no longer wish to receive these emails, click https://codeforces.com/unsubscribe/contests/51474b72d79ac8ec8363936f1ca54cbe6dbb957a/ to unsubscribe.  Wish you high rating, MikeMirzayanov and Codeforces team

Subject: Learn high-performance C and C++ programming [Free 6-hour course]
"Kiếm bạn đi ăn chung?"
📊 Python for Data Analytics is available now!
Body: Dear B22DCAT251 Dang Duc Tai,   We're excited to release course three in the Data Analytics Professional  Certificate: Python for Data Analytics    This comprehensive course introduces you to Python—the most widely used  programming language among data professionals—with no prior coding  experience required.         * Begin with programming fundamentals in an interactive Jupyter         notebook environment, the open source format used by data         professionals         * Learn to organize and manipulate data with pandas, a data analysis         library, to create powerful analyses that would be slow or         impossible in spreadsheets         * Build high-quality visualizations that can reveal hidden patterns         in your data         * Apply statistical tests and regression analysis to draw         evidence-based conclusions         * Analyze time series data to identify trends and make forecasts   Unlike tutorials that just show perfect code, this course includes  troubleshooting sessions where you'll learn to diagnose and fix common  errors—an essential skill in real-world data work.   Python is the language of choice for data professionals—88% choose Python  for data science and statistical modeling, according to Kaggle’s State of  Data Science and Machine Learning survey (2022).   With data skills in high demand across industries, learning Python  positions you to solve real-world problems, grow your analytical expertise,  and advance your career.   Enroll today!    Keep learning,   The DeepLearning.AI team   DeepLearning.AI You are receiving this email because jaycedang0601@gmail.com is registered  for promotional emails from DeepLearning.AI on Coursera. Please do not reply directly to this email. If you have any questions or  feedback, please visit our learner help center   . Subject: The Byte: Get ready for a bootcamp🛡️climb to the top of a league, and new rooms!
Body: TryHackMe ( https://tryhackme.com/r/hacktivities?utm_source=cio&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=byte )Unlock cutting-edge training & insights  Continue Learning ( https://tryhackme.com/r/hacktivities?utm_source=cio&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=byte )   ( https://tryhackme.zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_qUijzzr7SjCqZusurw_7gg )  ************************** Master Microsoft Sentinel: Azure Bootcamp 101 **************************  Level up your training with our 45-minute Azure Bootcamp. Learn to deploy Microsoft Sentinel and leverage its powerful capabilities to detect, investigate, and respond to threats.      Seats are limited, so claim yours now!  Register Now ( https://tryhackme.zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_qUijzzr7SjCqZusurw_7gg )  Here's this week's pop quiz:  What is the primary purpose of Microsoft's "Azure Active Directory"?  * Cloud-based identity and access management * Virus protection for Windows devices * File storage and backup services Find the correct answer at the bottom of the newsletter 👀     *************************************** Have you joined our new Weekly Leagues? ***************************************  We've just launched a new way to challenge yourself, get badges and points: Weekly Leagues.   Complete 2 rooms and be automatically entered in a League along with 30 other users.  Climb to the top ( https://tryhackme.com/leagues?utm_source=cio&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=bytebeg_11apr25 ) ( https://tryhackme.com/leagues?utm_source=cio&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=bytebeg_11apr25 )   We want to congratulate some more users who are now SAL1 certified ( https://tryhackme.com/certification/security-analyst-level-1?utm_source=cio&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=byte_beg11apr25 ) 🏅  CyberStory.net  ByteTheIO  jackysim99  Here's a comment from Christian (ByteTheIO): "If you're looking to move into a SOC Analyst role, I highly recommend this hands-on certificate."     ********************************* This week's newest beginner rooms *********************************  ( https://tryhackme.com/room/breakingcryptothesimpleway?utm_source=cio&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=byte_beg11apr25 ) Breaking Crypto the Simple Way  Launch walkthrough ( https://tryhackme.com/room/breakingcryptothesimpleway?utm_source=cio&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=byte_beg11apr25 ) Exploiting common cryptographic mistakes.  ( https://tryhackme.com/room/socl1alerttriage?utm_source=cio&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=byte_beg11apr25 ) SOC L1 Alert Triage  Launch walkthrough ( https://tryhackme.com/room/socl1alerttriage?utm_source=cio&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=byte_beg11apr25 ) Learn more about SOC alerts and build a systematic approach to efficiently triaging them.  ( https://tryhackme.com/room/compromisedwindowsanalysis?utm_source=cio&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=byte_beg11pr25 ) Compromised Windows Analysis  Launch walkthrough ( https://tryhackme.com/room/compromisedwindowsanalysis?utm_source=cio&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=byte_beg11pr25 ) Learn about some key forensic artifacts and solve an interesting case of a compromised Windows workstation.  Continue learning ( https://tryhackme.com/r/hacktivities?utm_source=cio&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=byte )   This newsletter was brought to you by the TryHackMe Marketing team.     That's all from us — thank you for reading!     Lorena Gallo  Lifecycle Marketing Manager  Lorena Gallo  Lifecycle Marketing Manager  📝 The quiz answer is a. Subject: You have 1 new invitation
Body: You have 1 new invitation View invitations:https://www.linkedin.com/comm/mynetwork/?lipi=urn%3Ali%3Apage%3Aemail_email_notification_digest_01%3BUIQB8yGGRk2GOh7Au%2F5lfA%3D%3D&midToken=AQEMCMuQJusoZg&midSig=3xXgexb5fRDrI1&trk=eml-email_notification_digest_01-notification_card_MY_NETWORK-0-null&trkEmail=eml-email_notification_digest_01-notification_card_MY_NETWORK-0-null-null-i8mwdi~m9cqp7rh~1j-null-null&eid=i8mwdi-m9cqp7rh-1j&otpToken=MTMwNDFlZTIxYTI3Y2ZjMGJjMjgwZmViNDExYWUzYjc4OGNkZDE0MTljYTY4OTYzN2JjZjA1NjY0OTVkNWJmMGYzZDZkN2U5NmRmMWJmODU0N2FiZDViZjI5ZDNkNDNhNDM5NTNmYjcyMGU4MzMyZDliMGUzYzI1LDEsMQ%3D%3D    Le Uyen Thao shared a post: 11.04.2025  AI giờ đã có trí nhớ dài hạn. Và nếu điều đó không khiến bạn thấy lạnh sống lưng, có lẽ bạn chưa hiểu chuyện gì đang xảy ra.  ChatGPT giờ đây có khả năng ghi nhớ dài hạn, không chỉ trong một phiên trò chuyện, mà xuyên suốt nhiều lần tương tác – điều trước đây chưa từng có với mô hình ngôn ngữ lớn (LLM).  Trong kinh tế, vốn con người = trí nhớ + trải nghiệm + năng lực tái tạo tri thức. Điều này, trên lý thuyết, là bước chuyển từ generation sang accumulation. Từ phản ứng… sang kiến tạo.  Một AI có ký ức chính là hình thức mới của trí tuệ nhân tạo tích lũy – không khác gì dữ liệu nội tại của một tổ chức, hay “vốn tri thức mềm” mà mỗi quốc gia đang xây dựng.  Và khi AI bắt đầu tích lũy ký ức, chúng ta không chỉ bước sang một kỷ nguyên mới. Chúng ta đang bước vào trò chơi mà luật chơi không còn do con người quyết định hoàn toàn. Subject: Unleash Your Inner Ethical Hacker with CEH v13 AI!
Body: Hello Jayce,  Thank you for your inquiry regarding the Certified Ethical Hacker (C|EH) v13 AI program. We’re thrilled to introduce you to C|EH v13 AI, the first ethical hacking certification that integrates AI-powered tools and techniques. This program will equip you with cutting-edge skills to master both traditional and AI-driven ethical hacking methodologies, keeping you ahead in the ever-evolving field of cybersecurity. Key Highlights of C|EH v13 AI:    *   AI Integration: Automate tasks such as threat detection, vulnerability analysis, and anomaly detection for up to 40% greater efficiency.   *   Comprehensive Ethical Hacking: Master all five phases—Reconnaissance, Scanning, Gaining Access, Maintaining Access, and Covering Tracks—with AI support.   *   Cutting-Edge Content: 550 attack techniques, 221 labs, and real-world hacking tools to prepare you for modern cybersecurity challenges.   *   Global Recognition: Accredited by ANAB under ISO/IEC 17024, recognized by the U.S. DoD (8140/8570), and mapped to 45+ cybersecurity job roles.   *   Advanced Techniques: Learn about AI-based malware, deepfake attacks, and vulnerabilities in IoT and cloud systems. What You’ll Get with CEH v13 AI:    *   Guided Video Learning: 25+ hours of expert-led video instruction.   *   E-Courseware: 1-year access to detailed lab materials, covering 519+ attack techniques.   *   Hands-On Labs (iLabs): 6 months of access to core labs, with an optional upgrade to 130 self-study labs.   *   Certification Exam Vouchers: Includes CEH Theory and CEH Practical Exam vouchers (valid for one year).   *   Exam Retake: One free retake for the CEH Theory Exam.   *   Additional Resources: Practice Cyber Range, CEH Compete, Ethical Hacking Library, and more. Pricing Details:    *   Limited-Time Offer enroll now: 799 USD. where as the original price is 3000 USD. Don’t miss this opportunity to earn three certifications—C|EH, C|EH Practical, and C|EH Master—for a single discounted price. If you’re ready to proceed, I’d be happy to share the Student Enrollment Form (SEF) and payment details. Looking forward to assisting you in advancing your cybersecurity career. Subject: Unlock Your Future with Cisco: Watch Our Exclusive CCNA Session!
Body: A Glimpse at Your Future with the CCNA Experience an exciting opportunity to dive into the transformative journey of becoming a Cisco Certified Network Associate (CCNA). Uncover the potential career pathways that await you and see how this certification can open doors to new opportunities. Why Attend Career Opportunities: Learn about the diverse roles and tasks awaiting you as a CCNA Junior Engineer. Exam Preparation Tips: Get practical advice on preparing for the CCNA exam with resources like Cisco Press and Cisco U. Expert Insights: Gain valuable advice from industry leaders Hank Preston and Patrick Gargano as they guide you through the CCNA journey. Meet the Speakers Hank Preston Principal Engineer with Learning and Certifications Cisco Patrick Gargano Lead Content Advocate with Learning & Certifications Cisco Don't miss this chance to shape your future and open doors to exciting career opportunities. Join us and be part of a transformative experience.   <[[${FacebookLink}]]>  <[[${YoutubeLink}]]>  <[[${TwitterLink}]]>  <[[${LinkedInLink}]]>   Join our feeds to be the first to hear about updates and opportunities, and share your own innovative ideas.  Please do not reply to this email.   To unsubscribe, log in to Cisco Networking Academy , click on your name (top right corner), and update your Notification and Email Preferences. If you are no longer part of the Networking Academy program and need to have your account deleted, log in, go to help, and submit a request for deletion. Subject: Vietnam Consumer Evolution: Growth, Spending & Digital Shifts
Body: Vietnam Dynamic  By Thái Vân Linh   By Thái Vân Linh                Read this article on LinkedIn to join the conversation Read on LinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/comm/pulse/vietnam-consumer-evolution-growth-spending-digital-shifts-v%C3%A2n-linh-hcbhc?lipi=urn%3Ali%3Apage%3Aemail_email_series_follow_newsletter_01%3BLZOJqCANQnauhOOhTHyuag%3D%3D&midToken=AQEMCMuQJusoZg&midSig=1BwBkVZGD7AbI1&trk=eml-email_series_follow_newsletter_01-null-0-read_more_banner_cta_&trkEmail=eml-email_series_follow_newsletter_01-null-0-read_more_banner_cta_-null-i8mwdi~m99e67gb~a6-null-null&eid=i8mwdi-m99e67gb-a6&otpToken=MTMwNDFlZTIxYTI3Y2ZjMGJjMjgwZmViNDExYWUzYjU4OGNlZDc0MTllYWU4NjZmN2JjZjA1NjY0OTVkNWJmMGYzZDZkN2U5NDRkMmJhODI1MmYzZDI4MjA3YmMyMWE4YTc4MWMwYzhkYTg3OTI2ZTI5M2VlZTdkLDEsMQ%3D%3D    TLDR: Vietnam’s economy grew 7.1% in 2024, surpassing government targets and reinforcing its position as one of ASEAN’s fastest-growing economies. Vietnam is on track to become the 25th largest economy globally by 2039, with GDP projected to reach USD1.4 trillion. 1. ECONOMIC GROWTH AND E-COMMERCE EXPANSION Vietnam’s economy displayed resilience and expansion in 2024, despite external challenges such as slower global growth and natural disasters. Vietnam’s GDP per capita rose from USD4,346 in 2023 to USD4,700 in 2024, reflecting the country’s expanding middle class. While retail revenue growth slowed to 6%, e-commerce saw a significant surge of 18%, reaching USD22 billion, making Vietnam the third-largest e-commerce market in Southeast Asia. This rapid digital expansion, driven by mobile-first shopping behaviors and improved logistics infrastructure, positions Vietnam as a key player in the regional e-commerce landscape. 2. DEMOGRAPHIC SHIFTS AND MIDDLE-CLASS GROWTH With a population of nearly 101 million, Vietnam remains the third-most populous country in Southeast Asia. However, an aging population is emerging as a long-term economic consideration. By 2036, one in five Vietnamese will be a senior citizen, necessitating a shift in brand strategies and product portfolios. Meanwhile, income levels in both urban and rural areas continue to rise, with high and mid-high-income households contributing 60% of urban spending and nearly 50% in rural areas. The middle-class expansion is fueling consumer demand for premium products and services, particularly in healthcare, technology, and FMCG sectors. 3. OPPORTUNITIES IN RURAL MARKETS AND FMCG TRENDS Vietnam’s rural population accounts for 61% of the total consumer base, presenting a high-growth opportunity for FMCG brands. Rural FMCG spending has grown at a CAGR of 6% over the last five years, surpassing the 2% growth rate in urban areas. This trend narrows the spending gap between urban and rural consumers, signaling a shift in purchasing power beyond major cities. As consumer preferences evolve, businesses must adapt their product offerings and marketing approaches to cater to this expanding segment. Vietnam’s strong economic performance, expanding middle class, and rapid e-commerce adoption highlight its growth potential through 2025 and beyond. While demographic shifts pose challenges, businesses can capitalize on rising rural demand and digital commerce trends. With strategic adjustments, Vietnam remains well-positioned to achieve its long-term goal of becoming a high-income economy by 2045. Vietnam Consumer Evolution: Growth, Spending & Digital Shifts ===== TLDR: Nền kinh tế Việt Nam đạt mức tăng trưởng 7,1% vào năm 2024, vượt mục tiêu kỳ vọng của Chính phủ và củng cố vị thế như một trong những nền kinh tế phát triển nhanh nhất ASEAN. Việt Nam đang trên đà trở thành nền kinh tế lớn thứ 25 trên thế giới vào năm 2039, với GDP dự kiến đạt 1,4 nghìn tỷ USD. 1. TĂNG TRƯỞNG KINH TẾ VÀ SỰ MỞ RỘNG CỦA THƯƠNG MẠI ĐIỆN TỬ Nền kinh tế Việt Nam đã thể hiện khả năng phục hồi và mở rộng trong năm 2024, dù cho phải đối mặt với những thách thức bên ngoài như tăng trưởng toàn cầu chậm lại và thiên tai. GDP bình quân đầu người của Việt Nam tăng từ 4,346 USD vào năm 2023 lên 4,700 USD vào năm 2024. Điều này thể hiện sự mở rộng của tầng lớp trung lưu của quốc gia. Trong khi doanh thu bán lẻ chỉ tăng 6%, thì thương mại điện tử đã có mức tăng đáng kể 18%, đạt 22 tỷ USD, giúp Việt Nam trở thành thị trường thương mại điện tử lớn thứ ba Đông Nam Á. Sự bùng nổ kỹ thuật số, được thúc đẩy bởi hành vi mua sắm ưu tiên thiết bị di động và hạ tầng logistics được cải thiện, đưa Việt Nam trở thành một nhân tố chủ chốt trong trong bối cảnh thương mại điện tử khu vực. 2. CHUYỂN DỊCH NHÂN KHẨU HỌC VÀ SỰ MỞ RỘNG CỦA TẦNG LỚP TRUNG LƯU Với dân số gần 101 triệu người, Việt Nam vẫn là quốc gia đông dân thứ ba Đông Nam Á. Tuy nhiên, tốc độ già hóa dân số đang gia tăng, là một vấn đề liên quan đến kinh tế dài hạn đáng lưu ý. Đến năm 2036, cứ 5 người Việt thì sẽ có 1 người là công dân cao tuổi, việc này đòi hỏi phải có sự điều chỉnh các chiến lược thương hiệu và danh mục sản phẩm. Trong khi đó, mức độ thu nhập tại cả khu vực đô thị và nông thôn tiếp tục tăng, với các hộ gia đình có thu nhập cao và trung cao đóng góp 60% tổng chi tiêu ở thành thị và gần 50% ở nông thôn. Sự mở rộng của tầng lớp trung lưu đang thúc đẩy nhu cầu tiêu dùng các sản phẩm và dịch vụ cao cấp, đặc biệt trong các lĩnh vực chăm sóc sức khỏe, công nghệ và ngành hàng tiêu dùng nhanh (FMCG). 3. NHỮNG CƠ HỘI TẠI THỊ TRƯỜNG NÔNG THÔN VÀ XU HƯỚNG FMCG Dân số nông thôn chiếm 61% tổng số người tiêu dùng tại Việt Nam, tạo ra một cơ hội tăng trưởng mạnh mẽ cho các thương hiệu FMCG. Chi tiêu FMCG tại nông thôn đã tăng trưởng với CAGR 6% trong 5 năm qua, vượt qua tốc độ tăng trưởng 2% tại khu vực thành thị. Xu hướng này thu hẹp khoảng cách chi tiêu giữa người tiêu dùng thành thị và nông thôn, báo hiệu sự thay đổi trong sức mua ở các khu vực ngoài các thành phố lớn. Khi thị hiếu tiêu dùng thay đổi, doanh nghiệp cần điều chỉnh danh mục sản phẩm và các chiến lược tiếp thị để khai thác hiệu quả phân khúc đang mở rộng này. Việt Nam đang hướng đến sự tăng trưởng trong giai đoạn 2025 trở đi, nhờ vào hiệu suất kinh tế mạnh mẽ, sự mở rộng của tầng lớp trung lưu và sự phát triển nhanh chóng của thương mại điện tử. Dù sự chuyển dịch nhân khẩu học đặt ra những thách thức, các doanh nghiệp vẫn có thể tận dụng sự gia tăng nhu cầu tại khu vực nông thôn và xu hướng thương mại điện tử để mở rộng thị phần. Với các điều chỉnh chiến lược phù hợp, Việt Nam vẫn có thể duy trì vị thế tốt, để đạt mục tiêu trở thành nền kinh tế có thu nhập cao vào năm 2045. ===== Link to research Micro forces shaping consumer behaviour in 2025 Keep reading on LinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/comm/pulse/vietnam-consumer-evolution-growth-spending-digital-shifts-v%C3%A2n-linh-hcbhc?lipi=urn%3Ali%3Apage%3Aemail_email_series_follow_newsletter_01%3BLZOJqCANQnauhOOhTHyuag%3D%3D&midToken=AQEMCMuQJusoZg&midSig=1BwBkVZGD7AbI1&trk=eml-email_series_follow_newsletter_01-newsletter_content_preview_text-0-readmore_button_&trkEmail=eml-email_series_follow_newsletter_01-newsletter_content_preview_text-0-readmore_button_-null-i8mwdi~m99e67gb~a6-null-null&eid=i8mwdi-m99e67gb-a6&otpToken=MTMwNDFlZTIxYTI3Y2ZjMGJjMjgwZmViNDExYWUzYjU4OGNlZDc0MTllYWU4NjZmN2JjZjA1NjY0OTVkNWJmMGYzZDZkN2U5NDRkMmJhODI1MmYzZDI4MjA3YmMyMWE4YTc4MWMwYzhkYTg3OTI2ZTI5M2VlZTdkLDEsMQ%3D%3D            ----------------------------------------  This email was intended for Duc Tai Dang (--) Learn why we included this: https://www.linkedin.com/help/linkedin/answer/4788?lang=en&lipi=urn%3Ali%3Apage%3Aemail_email_series_follow_newsletter_01%3BLZOJqCANQnauhOOhTHyuag%3D%3D&midToken=AQEMCMuQJusoZg&midSig=1BwBkVZGD7AbI1&trk=eml-email_series_follow_newsletter_01-SecurityHelp-0-textfooterglimmer&trkEmail=eml-email_series_follow_newsletter_01-SecurityHelp-0-textfooterglimmer-null-i8mwdi~m99e67gb~a6-null-null&eid=i8mwdi-m99e67gb-a6&otpToken=MTMwNDFlZTIxYTI3Y2ZjMGJjMjgwZmViNDExYWUzYjU4OGNlZDc0MTllYWU4NjZmN2JjZjA1NjY0OTVkNWJmMGYzZDZkN2U5NDRkMmJhODI1MmYzZDI4MjA3YmMyMWE4YTc4MWMwYzhkYTg3OTI2ZTI5M2VlZTdkLDEsMQ%3D%3D You are receiving LinkedIn notification emails. Subject: Issue 272: On bubbles and revolutions
Body: The value of critical thinking, pointers vs. arrays, and getting AI to show IP  ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌          09 April    Hey, have you all heard of AI? I kid, I kid, but it's popular for a reason.  This week, we cover all sorts of angles on the topic du jour in today's  software industry. We chat with the CEOs of HumanX and Crunchbase about the  state of the AI industry. We chat with the field CTO of GitLab about how AI  best supports learning. We chat with folks at the HumanX conference about audio  models and LLM governance.   There's more to AI than just LLM, and we've got leads on that too. There's  info on the new role web data will play in LLMs. Our friends at Intuit talk  about an old-school AI technique they use to manage the NP-hard problem of  scheduling appointments at scale.   In other links, we've got the usual roundup of delicious info. Ponder the  math of roasted meats. Remember one of the code breakers who helped stop the  Nazis. Learn about the movement to develop web apps for local-first execution.  And argue whether there were CRT displays that could refresh faster than 60Hz.     From the blog   Using GenAI as a learning tool, not a crutch   stackoverflow.blog AI is changing how we think about coding. While tools evolve, critical  thinking, problem-solving, and creativity remain the essential skills for top  developers.  Is AI a bubble or a revolution? The answer is yes.   stackoverflow.blog At HumanX 2025, Ryan sat down with HumanX CEO Stefan Weitz and Crunchbase CEO  Jager McConnell to talk about where the money is in the AI space, where most  enterprise AI strategies fall short, how companies can build business models  when AI tech is evolving so quickly, and why this is AI’s microservices moment.  From training to inference: The new role of web data in LLMs   stackoverflow.blog Data has always been key to LLM success, but it's becoming key to  inference-time performance as well.  Not all AI is generative: Efficient scheduling with mathematics   promotion Efficiently solving a complex scheduling problem using simulated annealing.   Boots on the ground: Holistic AI and Audioshake at HumanX   stackoverflow.blog Two interviews for the price of one, direct from HumanX 2025! Ryan sits down  with Raj Patel, AI transformation lead at Holistic AI, and then chats with  Audioshake cofounder and CEO Jessica Powell.  50% of Kubernetes spend is wasted. Let’s change that.   promotion Get Kubernetes optimization with full visibility. Continuously and  autonomously optimize your Kubernetes environment for peak performance at the  lowest possible cost, and correlate that spend with your wider business  objectives. Learn how withDoiT.     Interesting questions   Why does K&R say that pointers are preferable to arrays as function parameters?    stackoverflow.com “Even if it was true at the time the book was written, there has been lots of  changes to CPUs and compilers since. ”  Is there a good reason why meat cooking times are generally quoted as linear  with respect to weight?   cooking.stackexchange.com Most cooks have a beef with complex math or are too chicken to try.  Were there any games running at high refresh rates such as 90 and 120 Hz on  computers and consoles of the 80s and 90s?   retrocomputing.stackexchange.com Two highly-reasoned answers with two different tl;dr conclusions.  How do I answer a technical interview question I am already familiar with?   workplace.stackexchange.com You don’t need to disguise the fact that you did your homework.     Links from around the web   What is local-first web development?   alexop.dev Very exciting to see web devs reinvent the desktop application.  The slow collapse of critical thinking in OSINT due to AI   www.dutchosintguy.com AI isn't the problem. Uncritical trust is.  An image of an archeologist adventurer who wears a hat and uses a bullwhip   theaiunderwriter.substack.com Unfortunately, copyright infringement leads to some cool things.  Bletchley code breaker Betty Webb dies aged 101   www.bbc.com Remembering one of the last of the WWII code breakers.   Looking for the tools, technologies, and skills your team needs to evolve in  the AI era?Stack Overflow's Industry Guide to AI    has your answers. Subject: Welcome to artoo
Body: Hello,  Thank you for signing up for artoo. We would love to hear your thoughts on how we can improve the platform. Please feel free to email David  or me (Daniel ) with any suggestions.  We are on a mission to build the best hacking tools for CTFers, bug bounty researchers, and for other members of the cyber security community alike! If you run into issues while crafting bug bounty exploits — and you’re up for grabbing a coffee in the NYC area — let us know!  Best, Daniel Chalco

Subject: Map your attack surface automatically (3/6)
Codeforces Round 1016 (Div. 3)
Body: Hello, Jayceee1.  You are welcome to register and compete in Codeforces Round 1016 (Div. 3). It starts on Tuesday, April, 8, 2025 14:35 (UTC). The contest duration is 2 hours 15 minutes. The allowed programming languages are C/C++, Pascal, Java, C#, Python, Ruby, Perl, PHP, Haskell, Scala, OCaml, Go, D, JavaScript, Rust and Kotlin.  Div. 3 rounds are designed especially for participants with a rating below 1600. We invite you to participate in the competition!  The goal of such rounds is to help beginner participants to gain skills and to get new knowledge in a real contest. You can read the details in this post dedicated to them. In short:  * Not only real problems, but also exercises can be used. * Our main goal is to give nice training problems, so we do not care much about the innovativeness of the problems. * Often the formal text of the statements. * Rated for participant with the rating below 1600. * ICPC rules + 12-hour open hacking phase. * Untrusted participants are not included in the official ranklist.  The round will be held on the rules of Educational Rounds, so read the rules (here) beforehand. The round will be for newcomers and participants with a rating below 1600. Want to compete? Do not forget to register for the contest and check your handle on the registrants page. The registration will be open for the whole contest duration.  If you have any questions, please feel free to ask me on the pages of Codeforces. If you no longer wish to receive these emails, click https://codeforces.com/unsubscribe/contests/51474b72d79ac8ec8363936f1ca54cbe6dbb957a/ to unsubscribe.  Wish you high rating, MikeMirzayanov and Codeforces team

 Andrew Ng shared a post: Contrary to standard prompting advice that you should give LLMs the context they need to succeed, I find it’s sometimes faster to be lazy and dash off a quick, imprecise prompt and see what happens. The key to whether this is a good idea is whether you can quickly assess the output quality, so you can decide whether to provide more context. In this post, I’d like to share when and how I use “lazy prompting.”  When debugging code, many developers copy-paste error messages — sometimes pages of them — into an LLM without further instructions. Most LLMs are smart enough to figure out that you want them to help understand and propose fixes, so you don’t need to explicitly tell them. With brief instructions like “Edit this: …” or “sample dotenv code” (to remind you how to write code to use Python's dotenv package), an LLM will often generate a good response. Further, if the response is flawed, hopefully you can spot any problems and refine the prompt, for example to steer how the LLM edits your text.  At the other end of the spectrum, sometimes  I spend 30 minutes carefully writing a 2-page prompt to get an AI system to help me solve a problem (for example to write many pages of code) that otherwise would have taken me much longer.  I don’t try a lazy prompt if (i) I feel confident there’s no chance the LLM will provide a good solution without additional context. For example, given a partial program spec, does even a skilled human developer have a chance of understanding what you want? If I absolutely want to use a particular piece of pdf-to-text conversion software (like my team LandingAI’s Agentic Doc Extraction!), I should say so in the prompt, since otherwise it’s very hard for the LLM to guess my preference. I also wouldn’t use a lazy prompt if (ii) a buggy implementation would take a long time to detect. For example, if the only way for me to figure out if the output is incorrect is to laboriously run the code to check its functionality, it would be better to spend the time up-front to give context that would increase the odds of the LLM generating what I want.  By the way, lazy prompting is an advanced technique. On average, I see more people giving too little context to LLMs than too much. Laziness is a good technique only when you’ve learned how to provide enough context, and then deliberately step back to see how little context you can get away with and still have it work. Also, lazy prompting applies only when you can iterate quickly using an LLM’s web or app interface It doesn’t apply to prompts written in code for the purpose of repeatedly calling an API, since presumably you won’t be examining every output to clarify and iterate if the output is poor.  Thank you also to Rohit Prsad, for suggesting the term lazy prompting. Subject: Kotlin Heroes: Episode 12 [100 t-shirts, money prizes!]
Body: Attention! The round starts on Monday, April, 7, 2025 14:35 (UTC).  Hello, Jayceee1.  We are happy to announce the twelfth "Kotlin Heroes" competition which will be held on Codeforces! Kotlin Heroes: Episode 12 is open for everybody, regardless of a division. We will be glad to see you among the participants!  It starts on Monday, April, 7, 2025 14:35 (UTC). The contest duration is 2.5 hours. You are allowed to use Kotlin only to solve the problems.  Register Now →  The round writers are BledDest, awoo, adedalic and Neon. Don't miss the round!  Top three winners will get prizes of $512, $256, and $128 respectively, top 50 will win a Kotlin Heroes t-shirt and exclusive Kotlin stickers, competitors solving at least one problem will enter into a draw for one of 50 Kotlin Heroes t-shirts.  Please note that we are not able to ship prizes to any country, state, province, or territory subject to comprehensive OFAC sanctions, including Belarus, Cuba, Iran, North Korea, Russia, Syria, or the Crimea, Donetsk, or Luhansk regions. For complete the list, please visit this page.  The round is held in accordance with slightly modified ICPC rules:  * The round is unrated. * The contest will have 6-10 problems of various levels of complexity. * You are allowed to only use Kotlin to solve these problems. * Participants are ranked according to the number of correctly solved problems. * Ties are resolved based on the lowest total penalty time for all problems, which is computed as follows. For each solved problem, a penalty is set to the submission time of that problem (the time since the start of the contest). An extra penalty of 10 minutes is added for each failed submission on solved problems (i.e., if you never solve the problem, you will not be penalized for trying that problem). If two participants solved the same number of problems and scored the same penalty, then those of them who had previously made the last successful submission will be given an advantage in the distribution of prizes and gifts.  Want to compete? Do not forget to register for the contest and check your handle on the registrants page.  To help you get familiar with Kotlin JetBrains has prepared a tutorial on competitive programming in Kotlin and a practice round, where you can try to solve a few simple problems in Kotlin. All solutions are open, which means that you can look at a solution even if you haven't solved a problem yet. The practice round is available by the link.  If you have any questions, please feel free to ask me on the pages of Codeforces. If you no longer wish to receive these emails, click https://codeforces.com/unsubscribe/contests/51474b72d79ac8ec8363936f1ca54cbe6dbb957a/ to unsubscribe.  Wish you high rating, MikeMirzayanov and Codeforces team

It’s time to rethink stress.   Turns out, stress isn’t all bad. It can help us stay safe, build resilience,  and stay connected to what matters. During Stress Awareness Month in April,  here are three tips to stress smarter:    💙 Take a minute (often)  💙 Deep breaths are your greatest ally  💙 Practice saying “I’m at capacity”    Feel better inside and out with 40% off Calm  A Calm Premium subscription gives you all the tools you need to feel better in  your pocket. Subject: Collab on videos (2/8)
Body: Making videos is better as a team. Sometimes you just need to create alone. But you can always invite someone else to join — a friend, co-worker, or client. But you can always invite someone else to join — a friend, co-worker, or client. Collaborate on any content, any time.         Review Mode  Invite as many reviewers as needed to share feedback on the project timeline — from any device. Finally, a way to avoid the feed-back and forth.  Invite someone   ( http://clicks.veed.io/f/a/1QFeXDF8v4qD7EUOzOghSQ~~/AAAHahA~/YESBtIfJACuBeNSy7beMl0AA97ehkXgdFHOI95vQn9zpggL2w1KivBMJWq4DwmH8MISkLntIdFC2CzzT1pkiCgWgJzS1bb1BQWE8crdXrB0logGh1B92i7ika2MPBU4skV00I7uvZcFCGdYC8UwC2ros9Vp97wBAw1Bdy1gi9gtA1M8FTUjWU_w53dUHbDQPqClOyYWdNfZ5XL_d4cw7E15IPLb0lZjYenNWRTADQDc~ )               Inviting someone to collaborate on your project is easy  * On your project, click * Type their email address and select ”Workspace Editor” or ”Reviewer " * Click so they get an email invitation with your video in it That’s all it takes! Subject: Next steps in your bug bounty journey!
Body: [Image "Schermafbeelding+2022-09-15+om+19.21.55.png?expires=1759300074&signature=f5e9a5bd52f23d88cef3c6068bfee73af99cf4d886ab100c77cfde0aa6aeb9ff&req=cSgmFsB7moVYFb4S23SwhXOtMmjKR8cOBK2A0wDe3WTzdQNG7w%3D%3D%0A"]   Welcome to the Intigriti community, Jayce Dang!   We are happy to have you on board and would like to share the next 5 steps that will help you become a successful bug bounty hunter!   1. Join the conversation   Want to meet and talk to other Intigriti community members? Join our Discord server to chat about bug bounties, CTF's, Intigriti challengers and more!   Join our Discord server   2. Follow us on X for news, tips and tricks!   Did you know that Intigriti's X account curates the best tips and tricks from the community in a series of #bugbountytips? Follow us on Twitter to get the latest buzz:   Follow @intigriti   3. Get ID checked to get access to more programs!   Did you know that you are 80% more likely to be invited to private programs if you are ID checked? Some companies even require it to send in a submission, and you'll need it to claim any payouts you'll receive on the Intigriti platform. Getting ID checked should only take 2 minutes.   Get ID checked   4. Check out our free educational resources on YouTube   Every week, we upload new educational videos to our YouTube channels, covering hacking techniques from beginner to expert level. Subscribe to our YouTube channel to get informed.   Subscribe to our YouTube channel   5. Subscribe to our researcher newsletter   Joining the bug bounty community can be a bit overwhelming in the beginning, there's just so much to catch up with! The Intigriti team is here to help: our community curated newsletter Bug Bytes provides you with an overview of everything that has happened in the bug bounty space over the course of a week.   Subscribe to our researcher newsletter   You are receiving this one-time email because you have signed up to the Intigriti platform.

Subject: Teza Round 1 (Codeforces Round 1015, Div. 1 + Div. 2) (Rated for Everybody, prizes!)
Body: Attention! The round starts on Saturday, April, 5, 2025 14:35 (UTC).  Hello, Jayceee1.  I'm glad to invite you to take part in Teza Round 1 (Codeforces Round 1015, Div. 1 + Div. 2). It will be a joint round for Div.1 and Div.2 participants. The round will be rated for all participants. The contest duration is 3 hours. The allowed programming languages are C/C++, Pascal, Java, C#, Python, Ruby, Perl, PHP, Haskell, Scala, OCaml, Go, D, JavaScript, Rust and Kotlin.  Teza, founded in 2009 as a high-frequency trading firm, has evolved into a leading systematic quantitative hedge fund. From equities to options, futures, and crypto, they transform complex mathematical concepts into financial strategies that operate across the world's largest markets. You can read more about Teza in here. If you want to join the Teza, fill out this form.  Register Now →  The round writers are CharlieV and zltzlt. Don't miss the round!  Participants will have a chance to win Teza sticker packs and T-shirts:  * The top 25 ranked competitors. * 25 randomly selected from places 26-100.  The round will be held on the rules of Codeforces, so read the rules (here and here) beforehand. The round will be for newcomers and participants from the both divisions. Want to compete? Do not forget to register for the contest and check your handle on the registrants page. The registration will be closed 5 minutes before the contest.  If you have any questions, please feel free to ask me on the pages of Codeforces. If you no longer wish to receive these emails, click https://codeforces.com/unsubscribe/contests/51474b72d79ac8ec8363936f1ca54cbe6dbb957a/ to unsubscribe.  Wish you high rating, MikeMirzayanov and Codeforces team

Launch Careers Quiz ( https://tryhackme.com/careers/quiz?utm_source=cio&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=byte_beg4apr25 )  Here's this week's pop quiz:  What skill is most essential for an entry-level Security Operations Center (SOC) Analyst?  * Advanced software development * Threat detection and log analysis * Hardware repair and maintenance Find the correct answer at the bottom of the newsletter 👀    We want to congratulate some more users who are now SAL1 certified ( https://tryhackme.com/certification/security-analyst-level-1?utm_source=cio&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=byte_beg4apr25 ) 🏅  Yennefer.28  kush.borikar  .Lucky. Subject: [Dreamhack] It’s a good day to CTF
Body: Dreamhack CTF Season 7 #7 < It’s hard to pick the perfect outfit for erratic weather >       Hey Jaycelation,  Greetings from Dreamhack, the hacker’s playground!    Spring’s finally here, and so is the chaos of dressing for it. One day it’s freezing, the next it’s borderline summer – the weather’s all over the place, and picking an outfit is basically a guessing game.  But while you're dodging temperature swings, we’ve got another kind of challenge lined up: This week’s Dreamhack CTF is full of tricky problems to match the mood. And for those who crack them with style? We’ve got a reward waiting.      Score high, and you’ll win our newest Dreamhack umbrella – featuring the triple-fold Amo & Boko design. Rain or shine, you’ll be ready.  Good luck out there. Stay sharp (and dry).       * 🗓️ Schedule   * 2025/04/05 09:00 ~ 23:59 (15hrs, UTC+9)    * 🚩 Eligibility   * All Dreamhack Members    * ❓ Challenge Categories   * Pwnable(Crypto), Reversing, Web, Crypto    * ☂️ Prizes   * Dreamhack Umbrella   * 1 CTF Winner    * 4 Lucky Draws (Min. 1 solve required!)    * Prize draws will be held at the #dh-ctf-season7 channel of the   [Dreamhack  Official Discord server]  https://discord.gg/dreamhackio   .   We can’t wait to see you all in action!  Happy Hacking!  - The Dreamhack Team    [Click to Participate] https://dreamhack.io/ctf/661  This email was sent to all Dreamhack members. Subject: Educational Codeforces Round 177 (Rated for Div. 2)
Body: Hello, Jayceee1.  The series of Educational Rounds continues thanks to the support of the Neapolis University Pafos. They offer a BSc in Computer Science and Artificial Intelligence. The JetBrains Foundation supports this bachelor's program and offers 20 fully funded scholarships for the most talented applicants. Learn more.  You are welcome to register and compete in Educational Codeforces Round 177. The round is based on the problems from the Open Championship of Karelia in competitive programming. It starts on Thursday, April, 3, 2025 14:35 (UTC). The contest duration is 2 hours.  Register Now → The round will be rated for ratings up to 2100.  The goal of educational rounds is to practice and educate, rather than to compete. You can read the details in this post dedicated to them. In short:  * Not only problems, but also exercises can be used. * Useful ideas will be reused to introduce them to a wider range of participants, even if they are well-known. * Often the formal text of the statements. * Rated for Div. 2, unrated for Div. 1. * ICPC rules + 12-hour open hacking phase.  The allowed programming languages are C/C++, Pascal, Java, C#, Python, Ruby, Perl, PHP, Haskell, Scala, OCaml, Go, D, JavaScript, Rust and Kotlin.  The round will be held on the rules of Educational Rounds, so read the rules (here) beforehand. The round will be for newcomers and participants from both divisions. But the difficulty of problems is for Div 2. Want to compete? Do not forget to register for the contest and check your handle on the registrants page. The registration will be open for the whole contest duration.  If you have any questions, please feel free to ask me on the pages of Codeforces. If you no longer wish to receive these emails, click https://codeforces.com/unsubscribe/contests/51474b72d79ac8ec8363936f1ca54cbe6dbb957a/ to unsubscribe.  Wish you high rating, MikeMirzayanov and Codeforces team
